meaning: suggests that you are closing yourself off from others. You are hesitant in letting others in and revealing your feelings. It is indicative of some fear and low self-worth. If someone slams the door in your face, then it indicates that you are feeling shut out or some activity or that you are being ignored.

context: In particular, seeing the front door in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are shielding yourself from outside influences.

context: To see revolving doors in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are literally moving in circles and going nowhere. You may feel that your opportunities and choices lead to a dead end.

context: To see a castle door in your dream
meaning: indicates that you have missed a huge and/or profitable opportunity, especially if you are standing outside the castle door. If you are standing inside the castle door, then it means that you have let your success and ego distance you from others.

context: Dreaming of a red door
meaning: refers to either anger or passion that you are keeping locked up within yourself. If you open the red door, then it means that you are confronting some uncomfortable emotions. To see a black door in your dream symbolizes your personal hidden secrets. If you open the black door, then it suggests that you are exposing yourself to danger. You are proceeding toward a situation despite the risk. Seeing a gray door in your dream indicates that you are experiencing ambiguity in your future.

context: To dream that you hear or ring a door bell
meaning: indicates that you are open to new experiences. The dream may also be calling attention to something that you have overlooked. Perhaps you do not yet realize that an opportunity is open to you.

context: To see a doorknob in your dream
meaning: symbolizes either access or restriction. Alternatively, the dream may suggest that you are not thinking intelligently. If you dream that the doorknob is talking, then it means that someone is always watching you. It also indicates that you are being underestimated in some way.

context: To see a doormat in your dream
meaning: indicates that you feel others are walking all over you and taking advantage you. Consider also if there is any message or words on the door mat as this will be significant in meaning.

context: To see a bricked-up doorway in your dream
meaning: implies that you are shutting yourself down from the world. If you are inside the bricked-up doorway, then it represents your sheltered life. If you are outside the bricked-up doorway, then it means that there is a deep secret that you are trying to prevent from coming out. Alternatively, a bricked-up doorway is similar to a locked door and signifies missed or denied opportunities.

context: To see your own doppelganger in your dream
meaning: is a reflection of your negative actions. The dream is showing you the consequences of your actions and what you should not do. Alternatively, the dream signifies bad luck, danger, and/or illness.

context: To dream that you are fighting with your doppelganger
meaning: means that you are struggling between good and evil and right and wrong. If you kill your own doppelganger, then it indicates that you have successfully repressed certain negative emotions from surfacing.

context: To dream that you are in a dormitory
meaning: represents the value you place on knowledge and education. You believe that you are constantly learning, even when you are not in the classroom. If you are currently a college student who live in a dormitory, then this symbol may just be a reflection of your current surroundings and hold similar meaning as a house.

context: To see dots in your dream
meaning: symbolize routine and monotony.

context: To see your own double in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are attempting to recapture the past and the good old times. Alternatively, the dream may indicate that you are needlessly working twice as hard or doing double duty.

context: To dream that you are on a double date
meaning: represents the dualities of your personality - the persona you show to the world and your true Self. Alternatively, the dream may simply mean togetherness and your need to socialize.

context: To see a double decker bus in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to consider alternatives to your way of thinking. Do not look at the situation or problem from a single perspective.

context: To dream that you are double jointed
meaning: refers to how you yield to the needs of others. You tend to go out of your way to help those who need it.

context: To see or work with dough in your dream
meaning: signifies potential, possibilities and the ability to create. The dream may also be a metaphor to symbolize money.

context: To see a doughnut in your dream
meaning: represents the Self. It suggests that you may be feeling lost and still trying to find yourself and your purpose in life. Alternatively, it refers to growth, development and nurturance. You are not yet completely whole.

context: To see a dove in your dream
meaning: symbolizes peace, tranquility, harmony, affection and innocence. In particular, to see a white dove in your dream represents loyalty, love, simplicity, gentleness and friendships. It may also signify a message and blessing from the Holy Spirit. You have let go of your thoughts of hate and revenge. If you dream that Jesus releases a white dove, then it refers to spreading the word of God.

context: To dream that doves are mating and building a nest
meaning: symbolize a joyous home life filled with love, tranquility, pleasure and security.

context: To see a dove fly away in your dream
meaning: suggests that someone you love has passed away.

context: To dream that you are moving down
meaning: suggests that you have made a wrong decision or headed toward the wrong direction in life. Alternatively, the dream may be a pun on "feeling down" or depressed. "Going down" may also sexual connotation and be a metaphor for oral sex.

context: To dream that you are making a down payment
meaning: symbolizes commitment. If you are dreaming of putting a down payment for a house, it means commitment to a relationship. If you are putting down a payment for a car, then it refers to your commitment toward a life goal.

context: To see or dream of a child with down syndrome
meaning: implies that you are underestimating your own abilities or someone else's.

context: Dreaming that you are going downhill
meaning: means that things are not going your way. You are experiencing some setbacks. Alternatively, the dream signifies regression or repressed thoughts.

context: To see a downspout in your dream
meaning: refers to suppressed emotions that are coming to the surface and needing to be addressed. It is symbolic of an emotional cleansing.

context: To dream that you are in downtown
meaning: represents your material concerns and possessions. It may indicate the hustle and bustle of your life.

context: To dream of a dowry
meaning: indicates hard work ahead for you. You need to overcome many obstacles in order to succeed.

context: To dream that you are dozing off
meaning: suggests that you are letting an opportunity is passing you by if you do not take action. You are lacking knowledge or awareness in some area or issue. You need to pay more attention to your surroundings.

context: To dream that you are Dracula
meaning: implies that you are draining the energy of others.

context: To see Dracula in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are being misguided in some area of your waking life. Be careful.

context: To dream that Dracula is your father
meaning: indicates that you feel a disconnect with your own father. You don't really know who is this man.

context: #Ref:vampire
meaning: #Ref:vampire

context: To feel a draft in your dream
meaning: indicates an external force that is affecting a situation or relationship in your life. It may also indicate a visitation of a Spirit or a communication from your subconscious.

context: To dream that you have been drafted
meaning: indicates that the opinions and beliefs of others are being forced upon you. You are feeling pressure from those around you who want you to do something that you are not comfortable with. Alternatively, it indicates your need for more self discipline in your life.

context: To see or use a drafting compass in your dream
meaning: represents your set path. You do not like to deviate from your plans, even if it is monotonous. Alternatively, a drafting compass symbolizes your drive for perfection.

context: To dream that you are dragging something
meaning: refers to your burdens and struggles. You need to unload and/or let go some of your responsibilities as it is holding you back. Perhaps it is a relationship that you need to let go of. Consider also what or who you are dragging. Alternatively, the dream may be a pun on a situation that is a "drag" or unpleasant.

context: Dreaming that you are being dragged
meaning: signifies a lack of power or control in the direction you are going. You are feeling forced to do something that you don't really feel like doing. Alternatively, being dragged symbolizes reluctance in some endeavor. Perhaps you are feeling unmotivated or uninspired. You are not doing your fair share.

context: To see or dream that you are a drag queen
meaning: refers to your over the top attitude. You are also exuding a lot of confidence. Alternatively, the dreams suggests that you are hiding your true self. Perhaps you are being someone who you are not.

context: To see or dream that you are in a drag race
meaning: refers to some situation that you don't really want to be involved in, but feel pressure to prove yourself. You have a strong competitive side. Alternatively, the dream means that you need to slow down before you jeopardize your well being.

context: To see a dragon in your dream
meaning: represents your strong will and fiery personality. You tend to get carried away by your passion, which may lead you into trouble. You need to exercise some self-control. If you dream about the birth of a dragon, then it refers to your emerging passion and strong will. In particular, dreaming of a metal dragon signifies an unyielding character, a water dragon symbolizes quiet confidence, a wood dragon means an analytical and logical mind, a fire dragon refers to a competitive nature and leadership and an earth dragon signifies sociability.

context: Dragon
meaning: In the eastern cultures, dragons are seen as spiritual creatures symbolizing good luck and fortune.

context: To dream that you are a dragon and breathing fire
meaning: suggests that you are using your anger to get your own way.

context: To see a dragonfly in your dream
meaning: symbolizes change and regeneration. It may also indicate that something in your life may not appear as it seems. Alternatively, the dream represents instability flightiness or activity. You are always on the go.

context: To dream that you are eating a dragonfly
meaning: suggests that you are consumed by some sort of passion even at the risk of offending or hurting other's feelings.

context: To see a drain in your dream
meaning: signifies your need to release and channel your emotions. You should not keep your feelings inside. Consider the condition and appearance of the drain for clues on how you are feeling. Alternatively, it may represent some wasted effort or loss. The dream may also be a pun on something or someone that is "draining" you of your energy or resources.

context: To dream that you are unclogging the drain
meaning: indicates that you need to remove some obstacle or blockage that is hindering your progress.

context: To see a drainer in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are getting rid of your excessive emotions. Or on the other hand, it could imply that you are feeling emotionally drained.

context: To dream that you are in drama class
meaning: signifies your ability to express your emotions. The dream may be a metaphor for your waking life. Do you feel like you are living in your own drama?

context: To dream that you are closing the drapes
meaning: suggest that you are blocking out external worries and problems. You are shielding yourself from the world.

context: To see a drawbridge in your dream
meaning: represents protection. You feel that some relationship or situation is too invasive. It may also mean that you are drawing the line and creating boundaries.

context: To see drawers in your dream
meaning: signify your inner and hidden state and being. In particular, a disorderly drawer represents internal chaos and turmoil while an orderly drawer signifies calmness. Alternatively, a drawer symbolizes your reserves. There is something that you have stored away, but are now ready to use or express. If the drawer is full, then it symbolizes your many resources. If the drawer is empty, then it denotes your need to fulfill your goals.

context: To dream that you are drawing
meaning: represents an expression of your latent artistic abilities. You need to show more of your creativity in your waking life. Alternatively, the dream may be a pun on a "draw" to mean a tie or some undecided decision or argument. "It's a draw."

context: If you do not have dreadlocks in your waking life and dream that you have them,
meaning: then it indicate a rejection of traditional values and beliefs. You are going against the norm of society. Alternatively, the dream may be a metaphor for something that you are dreading.

context: To dream of our website Dream Moods
meaning: indicates the importance you are placing in understanding dreams. You are serious about learning more from your dreams. Alternatively, it also represents of sense of community.

context: To see a dreamcatcher in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are putting up a wall or barrier against the negativity in your life. Perhaps there is something in your subconscious that you are trying to prevent from emerging.

context: To dream that you are dreaming or daydreaming
meaning: signifies your emotional state. You are excessively worried and fearful about a situation or circumstance that you are going through. Dreaming that you are dreaming also serves as a layer of protection from what you are feeling. The dream within a dream allows you to experience certain difficult feelings that may otherwise be too painful to confront if you were directly dreaming the scenario.

context: To see or wear a dress in your dream
meaning: represents a feminine outlook or feminine perspective on a situation. You are freely expressing your femininity. If you are a man and dream that you are wearing a dress suggests that others are questioning your sexuality. Or that you are feeling sexually insecure.

context: To dream that you are wearing a white dress
meaning: implies that you want to appear pure and angelic toward others. Perhaps you are trying to look "innocent". To dream that you are wearing a purple dress refers to your devotion to your spouse or partner. Dreaming of wearing a blue dress indicates a desire to fit in or be like someone else. If the dress is another color, look up the specific color for additional significance.

context: Dreaming that you are wearing a dress that belongs to someone has has passed away
meaning: suggests that you have not let go. You are trying to relive or hold on to something in the past.

context: To see a dress form in your dream
meaning: refers to your desires to fit in. You feel that you do not measure up to others ideals or expectations.

context: To see a dresser in your dream
meaning: represents aspects of yourself that you are hiding. It may refer to your intimate self or childhood self. You need to reevaluate these emotions and either discard or incorporate them into your daily life.

context: To dream that you are dressed in someone else's clothes
meaning: represents your admiration for that person. You are trying to incorporate aspects of that person into your own self.

context: To dream that you are dressing up
meaning: suggests that you need to be more confident in your abilities and proud of your achievements.

context: To dream that you are having trouble getting dressed
meaning: indicates that someone is trying to cause you problems and give you stress in your waking life.

context: To dream that you are dressed in white
meaning: indicates longevity, good health or purity. You are trying to appear innocent to others.

context: To dream that you are in a dressing room
meaning: suggests that you are trying to fit into some new situation or role. You are working on a fresh self-image. If the clothes do not fit, then it implies a feeling of insecurities. You feel you don't fit in. Alternatively, the dream represents your changing roles and the various personas you have.

context: #Ref:floating
meaning: #Ref:floating

context: To see a drill in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are headed toward a new direction in life. You are opening yourself up to new experiences and insights.

context: To dream that you are drinking water
meaning: represents spiritual refreshment. You will find resolution by looking within yourself and your past. Alternatively, the dream may indicate that you are really thirsty.

context: To dream that you are drinking alcohol
meaning: denotes that you are seeking either pleasure or escape. In particular, if you are drinking wine, then it is symbolic of a divine power.

context: #Ref:waterfountain
meaning: #Ref:waterfountain

context: #Ref:beverage
meaning: #Ref:beverage

context: To dream that something is dripping
meaning: suggests that you are slowly losing your spiritual will. You are experiencing something disturbing which is affecting your psyche and well-being.

context: To see or dream that you are at a drive-in
meaning: indicates that you are taking a different life path then you had planned. Perhaps you have put your own goals on hold. You may also be reflecting on certain decisions you have made in your life.

context: To dream that you are going through a drive-thru
meaning: implies that your ambition and drive is getting in the way of your personal relationships. Sometimes you need to take a break and reconnect with loved ones.

context: To see your driver's license in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are facing an identity crisis.

context: To lose your driver's license in your dream
meaning: indicates that you have lost your way or direction in life. Perhaps you have lost the autonomy to move forward toward your goals. Alternatively, the dream may mean that you have lost your true Self. You are trying to be someone you are not.

context: To see or drive up to a driveway in your dream
meaning: symbolizes an end to your journey. It also represents security and rest. Alternatively, it denotes your path toward achieving inner peace and finding your spirituality.

context: To see rocks on the driveway
meaning: refers to a rocky end to some journey.

context: To dream that you are driving a vehicle
meaning: signifies your life's journey and your path in life. The dream is telling of how you are moving and navigating through life. If you are driving and cannot see the road ahead of you, then it indicates that you do not know where you are headed in life and what you really want to do with yourself. You are lacking direction and goals. Similarly, to dream that you are driving at night suggests that you are unsure of where you are headed in life. You are experiencing obstacles toward your goals. Perhaps you do not want to see what is ahead for you or you are afraid to confront certain issues. You may be feeling apprehensive about the future. If your view is blocked or obstructed while you are driving, then it symbolizes your lacking awareness of something in your life. You are overlooking certain aspects in your life. Alternatively, the dream indicates dangers or problems that are not yet made known to you. If you are driving on a curvy road, then it indicates that you are having difficulties in achieving your goals and accepting the changes associated with it. If you are driving in the snow, then it means that you need to be extra cautious about how your approach your goals. Metaphorically, driving a car in your dream is analogous to your sex life and sexual performance. Consider how you are driving and what kind of car you are driving and how it relates to your waking sex life. Or the dream may be a pun on your "drive" or ambition.

context: To dream that someone else is driving you
meaning: represents your dependence on the driver. You are not in control of your life and following the goals of others instead of your own. If you are driving from the passenger side of a car, then it suggests that you are trying to gain control of the path that your life is taking. You are beginning to make your own decisions. If someone else is driving you from the passenger side, then it means that you are being misled into thinking that you are in power or that you are in full control.

context: To dream that you are driving a cab or bus
meaning: suggests that menial tasks are providing little opportunities for advancement. Dreaming that you are driving an ambulance indicates that you are putting the needs of others before your own. Perhaps you are letting others dictate your direction or goals in life.

context: To dream that you are driving a car in reverse
meaning: suggests that you are experiencing major setbacks in your goals. In particular, if you drive in reverse into a pool of water, then it means that you emotions are literally holding you back.

context: To dream that you are driving drunk
meaning: indicates that your life is out of control. Some relationship or somebody is dominating you.

context: To dream that you drive off a mountain road
meaning: suggests that the higher you climb in life, the harder it is to stay at the top. You feel that your advanced position is a precarious one. It takes hard work to remain at the top. You may also feel that you are not able to measure up to the expectations of others.

context: To dream that you are a backseat driver
meaning: means that you have problems relinquishing control. You have power issues.

context: Dreaming that you are driving fast
meaning: suggests that you need to slow down and think through your choices. You are so focused on your goals that you are leaving behind the people around you.

context: To dream that you are taking a driving test
meaning: suggests that your goals and aspirations are being put to the test. You may be questioning what you really want to do with your life. If you fail the driving test, then it indicates that you do not have the necessary tools to move toward your goals. You may be lacking confidence. If you pass the driving test, then it represents your motivation and confidence in your ability.

context: To see a dromedary in your dream
meaning: signifies unexpected gains and honor. You are a giving person and always there to lend a helping hand.

context: To dream that you are flying or controlling a drone aircraft
meaning: indicates that you need a new or better vantage point on something.

context: Seeing a drone aircraft in your dream
meaning: means that you need to take control of your goals and of your destiny.

context: To dream that you are drooling
meaning: suggests that you are feeling foolish or embarrassed by some situation. On the other hand, you may be taking things too seriously and need to let loose.

context: To dream that you or someone is lying in drool
meaning: symbolizes a sense of hopelessness.

context: To dream that you are dropping things
meaning: indicates that you need to let go of some project, relationship, person, or idea. Also analyze the significance of what is being dropped. Alternatively, it may represent your carelessness. Perhaps you are expressing some dismay or regret in how you let something slip through fingers.

context: To dream of a drought
meaning: indicates that you are void of emotions. You are withdrawn and depressed. The dream may be a result of a major loss in your life. Alternatively, the dream suggests that you are not drinking enough water and staying well hydrated.

context: To dream that you are drowning
meaning: indicates that you are feeling overwhelmed by emotions. Repressed issues may be coming back to haunt you. You may be proceeding too quickly in trying to discover your subconscious thoughts. You should proceed more cautiously and slowly. If you drown to death, then is refers to an emotional rebirth. If your survive the drowning, then it means that a waking relationship or situation will ultimately survive the turmoil.

context: To see someone drowning in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are becoming too deeply involved in something that is beyond your control. Alternatively, it represents a sense of loss in your own identity. You are unable to differentiate who you are anymore.

context: To dream that you rescue someone from drowning
meaning: indicates that you have successfully acknowledged certain emotions and characteristics that is symbolized by the drowning victim. Thus dreaming of rescuing a drowning baby means that you are allowing yourself to be vulnerable and accepting help from others. If you fail to make the rescue, then it implies that you are numb from fear. Consider a situation in your waking life where you are letting fear dictate your actions.

context: To dream that you are in possession of or taking drugs
meaning: signifies your need for a "quick fix" or an escape from reality. You may be turning to a potentially harmful alternative as an instant escape from your problems. Ask yourself why you need the drugs. What do you hope the drugs will achieve for you?

context: Dreaming of someone shooting up drugs
meaning: implies that others are not seeing things from your angle. You don't understand where others are coming from and feel that their perspective is skewed. Alternatively, the dream means that you are feeling helpless in a situation and don't know how to respond.

context: To dream that you or someone overdoses
meaning: suggests that you do not know your limits. You may be pushing yourself too hard. Alternatively, the dream means that you are on a self-destructive path and need to make some significant changes.

context: To dream that you are dealing or selling drugs
meaning: represents changes.

context: To dream that you have been drugged
meaning: indicates that you are refusing to take responsibility for your actions.

context: To dream that you are in a drugstore
meaning: signifies a time for healing. You need to correct your thinking and readjust your attitude. You should look within yourself for the solution to a problem instead of relying on outside help. Alternatively, you may also be experiencing concerns with your health.

context: To dream that you are playing the drums
meaning: indicate that you progress through life by your own terms. You are strong willed and stick by the decisions you make. The dream may also be a metaphor to indicate you are "drumming up" business. You need to be more aggressive with your new ideas.

context: To hear a drum in your dream
meaning: symbolizes the rhythm of life and the need to keep a steady pace in the pursuit of your goals.

context: To see a pair of drumstick in your dream
meaning: represents your power and determination. You are striving to make a difference. Alternatively, the dream means that you need to establish a rhythm and have more control in your life.

context: To dream that you are drunk
meaning: suggests that you are acting careless and insensible. You are losing control of your life and losing a grip on reality. Perhaps you are trying to escape from a waking situation.

context: To dream that you are at the dry cleaners
meaning: indicates that you are trying to be more objective in some situation. You are showing restraint and control over your emotions.

context: To see a dryad in your dream
meaning: points to your quiet, soft-spoken persona. Alternatively, the dream may refer to your environmental awareness or that you need to be more environmentally conscious.

context: To dream that you are using a dryer
meaning: suggests that you need to start dealing with your emotions. The dream may also signify a dry idea that fails to bring any excitement and thrill.

context: To see or install drywall panels in your dream
meaning: refers to your desires for privacy. You are building up a layer of protection. Perhaps you have been hurt and are being guarded with your emotions.

context: To dream of being in Dubai
meaning: symbolizes commerce, vision, success and imagination. You are of a creative mindset. Alternatively, dreaming of Dubai suggests that you are having a difficult time on focusing on one goal.

context: To see ducks in your dream
meaning: represent your spiritual freedom (if flying) or the subconscious (if swimming). They serve as a connection between the spiritual realm and the physical world. Ducks are multi-talented animals in that they can walk, swim and fly. Thus, a duck indicates your flexibility and your ability to blend and adapt in various situations. Alternatively, the dream suggests that you are setting yourself up or being set up for the kill as associated by the phrase "sitting duck". Are you being targeted? Also, the duck may be a pun on "ducking" some issue or situation, instead of confronting it head-on. Consider the phrase, "if it looks like a duck, walks like a duck, quacks like a duck, it's a duck". Some things are too obvious to deny.

context: To see a white duck in your dream
meaning: signifies falsehood and deceit.

context: To see a two-headed duck in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to be more grounded. You need to thoroughly think through some emotional issue.

context: To see a dead duck in your dream
meaning: refers to a pessimistic outlook. You are set on a path that is destined for doom.

context: To see or use duct tape in your dream
meaning: represents your strong hold or grasp of some situation. You are able to separate your feelings and be objective.

context: To dream that you are in a duel
meaning: signifies internal disagreements or inner conflicts in which you need to find a middle ground. You need to stop seeing things in black and white.

context: To sing in a duet in your dream
meaning: signifies balance and harmony. You are coming to terms with some problem or issue that you have been at odds at for a long time.

context: To see a dulcimer in your dream
meaning: signifies carefree attitudes and a life where your desires will be happily realized.

context: To dream that you are dumb
meaning: denotes your inability to persuade others to see your point of view.

context: To see or drive a dump truck in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to get rid of the burden that you have been carrying around with you. This dream symbol may be related to some major change.

context: To see a dummy in your dream
meaning: indicates that a critical component is lacking in your relationship. You are feeling unchallenged and unfulfilled. The relationship is making you feel empty. The dream may also point to how you or someone has acted foolishly and stupidly in a situation.

context: To see or eat dumplings in your dream
meaning: signify dietary balance. You need to take better care of your health.

context: To make or wrap dumplings in your dream
meaning: symbolizes tradition, family, and togetherness.

context: To dream that you are at a dumpster
meaning: implies that you may that you are being dumped on. You feel rejected. Alternatively, it indicates that you are trying to rid yourself of old, negative habits and bad characteristics.

context: To dream that you are secretly throwing something away in a dumpster
meaning: suggests that you are not taking responsibility for something.

context: To dream that you are a dunce
meaning: suggests that you are not thinking through your actions clearly. You are acting without thinking.

context: To see or ride a dune buggy
meaning: suggests that you need to find your own way in life and not follow someone else's path. Alternatively, dreaming of a dune buggy relates to your quest for adventure and life experiences.

context: To see cow dung in your dream
meaning: symbolizes fertility and renewal.

context: To dream that you are in a dungeon
meaning: represents your subconscious thoughts and wishes. Consider what you see or do in the dungeon. Alternatively, it indicates that you will overcome the obstacles in your waking life by continuing to struggle and utilizing your wisdom.

context: To see a dunghill in your dream
meaning: indicates that fortune will come from the most unexpected of sources.

context: To dream that you are dunking a basket
meaning: represents your achievements and goals. You are on the right track toward success and accomplishing your goals. Alternatively, if you play basketball in your waking life, then the dream may serve as "practice". If you visualize yourself dunking a basket, then you are more likely to achieve it. This is a technique utilized by many athletes.

context: To dream that you are sitting inside a dunk tank
meaning: suggests that you are on the verge of an emotional breakdown. You feel on edge. If you get dunked into the water in your dream, then it means that you are being forced to face your feelings.

context: Dreaming of hitting the target of a dunk tank
meaning: means that you are imposing your views and opinions on others.

context: To see or dream that you are in a duplex
meaning: suggests that you are feeling conflicted. In particular, if you dream that a school and a mall are located within a duplex, then it means that your time is torn between two obligations.

context: To see Durga in your dream
meaning: implies that your problems and difficulties will soon be over. Trust in your ability to overcome the negativity in your life. Alternatively, seeing Durga in your dream represents a birth (either an actual birth or birth of a new idea).

context: To see or eat durian in your dream
meaning: indicates that you should not judge others based on the outside. You never know what you will find if you get pass the exterior appearances. Alternatively, the dream may mean that some unpleasant memory or obstacle is trying to hinder your path to self discovery.

context: To see the dusk of day in your dream
meaning: signifies defeated hopes and a dark, gloom outlook in your endeavors.

context: To see dust in your dream
meaning: suggests that certain aspects of yourself have been ignored or neglected.

context: To dream that you are covered in dust
meaning: signifies that the failure of others will adversely affect you.

context: To dream that you are dusting
meaning: implies that you are clearing out all your past mistakes and starting fresh on a new slate.

context: To dream that gold dust is running through your fingers
meaning: indicates regrets with the ending of some personal relationship. You feel that you've made a terrible mistake.

context: To see a duvet in your dream
meaning: symbolizes protection. It may also indicate that you are sexually conservative. Consider the color or pattern of the duvet for more clues on the meaning.

context: To watch a DVD in your dream
meaning: indicates that you need to stop and relax. Take a break from life and let your mind rest. Consider the title of the DVD or what you are watching and determine how it relates to your waking life. Alternatively, the DVD represents your desire to recapture or relive a certain moment in your life.

context: To see a dwarf in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are well-grounded and connected to nature and the earth. Alternatively, a dwarf may mean an aspect of yourself that is not fully developed or has been repressed. You may be feeling inferior or insignificant.

context: To dream that you are dyeing your hair
meaning: indicates that you are trying to project a new persona. If you are dyeing your hair to a darker color, then it suggests that you want to be more serious. If you are dyeing your hair to a lighter color, then you are looking to be more livelier.

context: #Ref:death
meaning: #Ref:death

context: To see the letter "P" in your dream
meaning: is a pun on "pee" or urine. You need to better express your emotions.

context: To see or play Pac Man in your dream
meaning: represents some sort of habit or behavior that is taking over your daily life.

context: To see a pacifier in your dream
meaning: represents emotional nurturance. You are expressing a desire to escape from your daily responsibilities and demands.

context: To dream that you are sucking on a pacifier
meaning: implies that you are trying to "suck up to" someone in your waking life. It may also denote your immature attitude.

context: To dream that you are trying to pacify someone or something
meaning: indicates your ability to remain calm or objective in a situation. Others are looking onto you in a time a crisis.

context: To see a package in your dream
meaning: represents hidden creative energy, skills, and/or feelings. If you receive a package, then it indicates that you are acknowledging certain feelings or acquiring new resources. If you are giving or sending a package, then it suggests that you are projecting your feelings onto another instead of dealing with them.

context: To dream that you are packing
meaning: signifies big changes ahead for you. You are putting past issues to rest or past relationships behind you. Alternatively, it represents the burdens that you carry.

context: To dream that you are packing, unpacking and packing and unpacking again
meaning: represents chaos in your life. You are feeling overwhelmed with the various things you are juggling in your life. You are carrying around too many burdens and need to let go. Consider what unfinished business you have to tend to. Try to resolve these issues so they can finally be put to rest.

context: To dream that you are packing, but the more your pack, the more there is to pack
meaning: implies that you are weighed down by the endless responsibilities and expectations in your life. As a result, you are stuck in your current circumstances.

meaning: represents your frivolous pursuits. You are restrained from going after what you really want.

meaning: #Ref:rowboat

meaning: #Ref:rowing

context: If you are not a pagan, but dream that you are,
meaning: then it suggests that you are misdirecting or misusing your energy.

context: If you are a pagan and see another pagan in your dream
meaning: refers to an important message from a divine power. You are looking for guidance.

context: To see or read a page in your dream
meaning: signifies a summary of your life. It is a reflection of what you have done what where you are headed. Alternatively, it suggests that you are on the rebound from a broken relationship. Be careful not to jump into a hasty relationship with someone ill-suited for you.

context: To see a blank page in your dream
meaning: signifies unproductively. You are not doing anything or going anywhere in your life. You are stagnant state.

context: To dream that you are a page
meaning: refers to your lack of motivation. You are spending too much time on pleasure and fruitless activities.

context: To watch or dream that you are in a beauty pageant
meaning: refers to your own insecurities about your appearances. You are constantly comparing yourself to others and how you measure up to them. You may also be subscribing to society's unattainable standards of beauty.

context: To see a pager in your dream
meaning: suggests that someone is trying hard to communicate their thoughts to you. Someone is trying to get through to you one way or another. On the other hand, you may feel that someone is pushing their beliefs and ideas onto you.

context: To see a pagoda in your dream
meaning: represents your own sense of spirituality. You may be embracing something that you may not be familiar with. Alternatively, the pagoda symbolizes the phallus and thus have sexual connotations.

context: To see or carry a pail in your dream
meaning: indicates an improvement in your current situation. If the pail is filled, then it signifies abundance, love and wealth. If the pail is empty, then it means that you will overcome some loss or conflict. The dream may also be a pun on "pale."

context: To dream that you are in pain
meaning: suggests that you are being too hard on yourself, especially if a situation was out of your control. The dream may also be a true reflection of actual pain that exists somewhere in your body. Dreams can reveal and warn about health problems. Consider where the pain is for additional significance. If the pain is in your neck, then the dream may be a metaphor that you are literally being a "pain in the neck".

context: To dream that you are inflicting pain to yourself
meaning: indicates that you are experiencing some overwhelming turmoil or problems in your waking life. You are trying to disconnect yourself from your reality by focusing on the pain that you inflicted to yourself.

context: To see paint in your dream
meaning: symbolizes expression of your inner emotions. Consider the color of the paint and how the color makes your feel. It is this feeling that you need to express more in your waking life.

context: To mix paint in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are incorporating a little variety in your life.

context: If you see or touch wet paint in your dream,
meaning: then it implies that you are unsure about your feelings. It may also mean that whatever you are feeling is still very fresh or raw.

context: To dream that you are playing paintball
meaning: represents your competitive, but fun side. You have a chance to accomplish something great in an area of your life. However, you need to proceed carefully to avoid being ambushed or blindsided, especially by malicious coworkers, friends or enemies. If you are hit by a paintball, then it symbolizes a minor setback. Also consider the color of the paint for clues on your emotions.

context: To dream of stalking someone in paintball
meaning: signifies your eagerness to tackle a challenge.

context: If you are being stalked in paintball,
meaning: then it symbolizes hidden dangers.

context: To see or use a paintbrush in your dream
meaning: represents harmony and creativity. It is also symbolic of your artistic talents.

context: To dream that you are painting your house
meaning: indicates that you will experience success in a new project. You may even be promoted to a coveted position. You may be expressing your creativity. Alternatively, the dream indicates that you are covering up something. If someone else is painting your house, then it suggests that someone close to you is hiding something from you. Also consider the color of the paint to determine any additional significance. For example, red colored paint may imply painting the town red and releasing pent up excitement.

context: To dream that paint has gotten on your clothes
meaning: signifies that you are too easily offended by criticism about you.

context: To see a painting in your dream
meaning: represents creativity and your need for self-expression. The painting is symbolic of your intuition and inner realizations.

context: To dream that you are painting a picture
meaning: indicates that you need to express your creative side more.

context: To see a pair of something in your dream
meaning: represents the need for balance in your life. The pair may be symbolic of your life partner or soul mate.

context: #Ref:sleepover
meaning: #Ref:sleepover

context: To see or wear pajamas in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to relax and get some rest. In particular, if you dream that you are wearing pajamas in public, then it means that you are unaware of something important that may be right in front of you. You are drifting through life without fully paying attention to what is going on around you.

context: To see a palace in your dream
meaning: symbolizes wealth and prominence. You are ready to utilize your full potential.

context: If you are living in a palace,
meaning: then it signifies that success is right within your reach.

context: To dream that you are pale
meaning: symbolizes sickness, disaster or fear. Some situation or relationship is emotionally draining you.

context: To see or use a an artist's palette in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are not afraid to express your innermost emotions. Alternatively, dreaming about a palette means that you are being your true self or that someone is being their real self; the are not putting on any facade.

context: To see a pall in your dream
meaning: symbolizes death or the end of something. Alternatively, the dream indicates that you are trying to hide or suppress some emotion or aspect of your life that you are not ready to confront.

context: To dream that you raise the pall from a coffin
meaning: signifies bad news, bereavement, or grief. Alternatively, the dream suggests that you are ready to reveal some deep emotion.

context: To see a pallbearer in your dream
meaning: suggests denotes that you have to keep your temper in check.

context: If the pallbearer is carrying a coffin in your dream
meaning: then it reflects changes in your life. Perhaps you are transitioning into a new career, new home, or new life path.

context: To see a pallet in your dream
meaning: symbolizes industry and manual labor.

context: To notice your palm in your dream
meaning: represents your generosity and openness, especially if they are open. You are always willing to help others. If you dream that your palm is closed, then it means that there is something that you are trying to hide or shield. Alternatively, to dream of your palm means that you hold the power in your own hands. You have the knowledge within yourself to maximize your potential.

context: To dream that you are having your palms read
meaning: represent your life goals and ambition. The dream shows how you want to live your life and where you want to be headed.

context: To see a palm tree in your dream
meaning: represents tranquility, high aspirations, fame, victory, hopes, and longevity. It also symbolizes paradise and leisure. Perhaps you need to take time for a vacation and relaxation.

context: To dream that you are having palpitations
meaning: represent fears that you are not confronting in your waking life. You may also be nervous about something.

context: To see a pan in your dream
meaning: refers to your attitude and your stance on a particular situation. It may also represent criticism and anger. If the pan is made of glass, then it means that you being conscious and aware about a particular situation. You are also opening yourself up to criticism. As a receptacle, it symbolizes the womb.

context: To see a frying pan in your dream
meaning: represents completeness in love. Alternatively, it suggests that you need to start accepting the consequences of your actions. You may have found yourself in an inescapable situation.

context: To make or eat pancakes in your dream
meaning: represent gratification and pleasure in your current situation. You take pleasure and comfort in the simple things of life.

context: To see a panda in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are having difficulties coming to a compromise in a waking situation. You need to find a middle ground so that all parties involved will be satisfied. Alternatively, a panda is symbolic of your own childlike qualities or something that is cuddly.

context: To dream of a Pandora's box
meaning: indicates hope. You will soon experience a turn for the better. Alternatively, it symbolizes your curiosity, your subconscious thoughts and your need to express them.

context: To see a pangolin in your dream
meaning: means that you need to protect yourself from your own drive. You are moving forward too recklessly and need to think before taking action.

context: To dream that you are in a panic
meaning: indicates a lack of control and power in your life. You are feeling helpless in some situation or unable to make a clear decision. Calm down.

context: To see a pansy in your dream
meaning: symbolizes undying and never ending love. It may also mean thoughtfulness, remembrance and nobility of the mind. Alternatively, it suggests that you are being too gullible. Or that you are not standing up for yourself.

context: To see a panther in your dream
meaning: signifies lurking danger and enemies working to do you harm. It represents darkness, death, and rebirth. On a more positive note, panthers signify power, beauty and/or grace. Consider the feel of your dream to determine which meaning applies.

context: To see or wear panties in your dream
meaning: represent your feminine attitudes and feelings. It reflects a female point of view.

context: To dream that you are taking off your panties
meaning: signifies your ideas of sexuality. It may also indicate your need to get to the bottom of things. You may want to find a way out of a situation.

context: To see a pantomime in your dream
meaning: represents a time in your life when things were more carefree and spontaneous. Alternatively, the dream may be dramatically calling your attention to an area that you need to be more aware of.

context: To dream that you are a pantomime
meaning: indicates that your voice is not being heard. Or your actions are being misunderstood and misconstrued.

context: To see or open the pantry in your dream
meaning: means that you have many resources within your reach. There is help when you need it. If the pantry is bare or empty, then it points to an emotional void that you are experiencing in your waking life.

context: To see or wear pants in your dream
meaning: suggest that you are questioning your role in some situation. Consider the material and color of the pants for additional interpretation. Alternatively, the dream may be hinting at some sexual matter.

context: To dream that you are wearing velvet pants
meaning: signifies your sensual side.

context: To see or wear a pantyhose in your dream
meaning: represents alluring sexuality. Consider the color of the pantyhose. If it is nude or beige color, then it signifies your discreteness. If it is black, then it symbolizes your hidden sexuality waiting to be expressed. If it is red, then it represents overt sexuality. If the pantyhose is torn or have a run, then it indicates lacking self esteem and reduced self confidence.

context: To see or eat papaya in your dream
meaning: indicates a healthy sex drive.

context: To dream that you are getting a pap smear
meaning: indicates concerns with your body and/or sexuality. You are feeling insecure. Alternatively, the dream may just represent your anxiety about your pap smear results or that you are due for a pap smear.

context: To see a stack of papers in your dream
meaning: denotes overwhelming responsibilities and stress that you are having to cope with. You are not effectively dealing with the issues at hand.

context: To see crumpled paper in your dream
meaning: symbolizes abandoned ideas.

context: Dreaming of a piece of red paper
meaning: suggests that you need to communicate your anger in a more effective and rational manner. Alternatively, red paper is symbolic of luck, happiness and wealth.

context: To see a filled paper bag in your dream
meaning: denotes something that may appear ordinary on the outside but can be extraordinary inside. In other words, do not judge something or someone by outside appearances. Consider what is inside the bag for additional significance.

context: To see or fold a paper plane in your dream
meaning: represents your frivolous pursuits. You are wasting time with ideas that go no where.

context: To see or use a paper plate in your dream
meaning: represents temporary nourishment or rewards. You need to take advantage of an opportunity before it is gone forever.

context: To dream that you are writing on a paper plate
meaning: refers to a fleeting idea or a message that you need to quickly convey.

context: To see or use a paper towel in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are experiencing some temporary setbacks. You need to quickly clean up your past issues before you can move forward with your life.

context: To see or use a paper clip in your dream

context: To dream that you are a paparazzo

context: To see the paparazzi in your dream

context: To see or taste paprika in your dream
meaning: represents someone or something is trying to get your attention. Alternatively, dreaming about paprika is a warning of seeing a different side of a person when they are angry.

context: To see a papyrus in your dream
meaning: indicates that you need to look to the past order to learn from it.

context: To dream that you are in a parachute
meaning: represents a protective force over you. You have a sense of security. Alternatively, the dream implies that it is time to bail out of a situation or abandon an old idea or habit.

context: To dream that you have difficulties with a parachute or that the parachute does not open
meaning: suggests that you are let down by someone you relied on and trusted. You feel abandoned.

context: To dream that you are watching a parade
meaning: indicates that you are being sidetracked or distracted from achieving your goals. You may even be purposely preventing yourself from pursuing your goals and desires because you fear that you will fail. Alternatively, the parade symbolizes cycles, passage of time, or a special event in your life. Consider also the symbolism of whatever figures/animals/floats are in the parade. They may reflect a need for you to incorporate these attributes into your own character.

context: To dream that you are in a parade
meaning: indicates that you are going along with the masses and with what everybody else wants. Alternatively, the dream indicates that you have a set path in life and know which direction you want to go.

context: To dream that you are in paradise
meaning: symbolizes your desire to achieve spiritual perfection. Your dream is expressing a desire to retreat from the stresses of the real world. Alternatively, it indicates that you are living in your own world. You are not being realistic.

context: To see a parakeet in your dream
meaning: indicates that you lack initiative and new idea. You need to be more unconventional and spontaneous. The dream also relates to dependency and immaturity.

context: To see a

context: To dream that you are in a

context: To dream that you are paralyzed
meaning: reflects the current state of your body while you are dreaming. During the REM state of sleep, your body is really immobile and paralyzed. People report that they cannot run or hit, despite how hard they try.

context: Symbolically, dreaming that you are paralyzed
meaning: means you are feeling helpless or pinned down in some aspects or circumstances of your waking life. You may feel unable to deal with a situation or change anything. Alternatively, the dream suggests that you are feeling emotionally paralyzed. You have difficulties expressing your feelings.

context: To see the paramedics in your dream
meaning: signify an issue that you need to address immediately before it gets to a critical state. You have been avoiding the problem for too long. Alternatively, the dream may mean that there is a situation or relationship that you need to "revive".

context: To dream that you are paranoid
meaning: indicates your hesitance in moving forward in some situation or relationship. You are so overcome with fear and suspicion that you are not ready to take that major step in your life.

context: To dream that objects are moving on its own or that switches and electronics are turning on/off or some other paranormal activity
meaning: indicates that you are refusing to take responsibility for your actions. The dream is also saying that you tend to let things happen instead of making things happen.

context: To see a parasite in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are feeling physically drained. You are becoming too dependent on others and experiencing a significant loss of vitality. Alternatively, a parasite refers to your tendency of taking without giving back.

meaning: suggests that you need to be more forgiving in some situation.

context: To see your parents in your dream
meaning: symbolize both power, shelter, and love. You may be expressing your concerns and worries about your own parents. Alternatively, it represents the merging of the female and male aspects of your character.

context: To dream about the death of your parents
meaning: indicates that you are undergoing a significant change in your waking life. Your relationship with your parents has evolved into a new realm.

context: Dreaming about your friend's parents, even though you may have never met them,
meaning: refers to your wishes of how you want your own parents to be like.

context: To dream that you are in Paris
meaning: symbolizes your need for romance and passion. It also suggests that you are a person of distinction. You own personal experiences and knowledge of Paris will supersede the suggested interpretation here.

context: To dream that you are at a park
meaning: represents a temporary escape from reality. It indicates renewal, meditation, and spirituality. You may be undergoing a readjustment period after experiencing some serious personal conflict or an end to a passionate affair.

context: To dream that you are lost in a park
meaning: indicates your struggles with your career, relationship, or other problem. You may feel alienated by society.

context: To dream that you are parking your car
meaning: represents your desire to settle down. Alternatively, it means that you feel accomplished in your goals and satisfied with your life. If you have difficulty parking the car, then it means that you are in some sort of a rut. You are feeling restless. Perhaps you wished you had taken a different path in your life.

context: To dream that you parked your car in a non-parking zone
meaning: suggests that you are poking your head in places where you do not belong. If you forgot where you parked, then it indicates that you have lost your direction in life. You are going off track.

context: To see or dream that you are a park ranger
meaning: represents control of your subconscious. You are also keeping your emotions in check.

context: To dream that you are a parking attendant
meaning: indicates that you are lacking your own direction in life. You are always helping others with their goals.

context: To dream that you are in parking lot
meaning: suggests that you need to slow down and take time from your daily activities.

context: To dream that you cannot find a parking space
meaning: indicates your inability to find your place in life. You may still be searching for your niche. Alternatively, the dream may reflect your busy life and the lack of time you have.

context: To see a parking meter in your dream
meaning: indicates that your leisurely and carefree days are soon coming to an end. You need to decide on a goal and what you want to do with your life before your time runs out. Alternatively, a parking meter suggests that you need to adjust your attitude or run the risk of offending others.

context: To see or dream that you are in a parking structure
meaning: suggests that you are going around in circles in some area of your life. You are feeling lost in what you want to do. If you cannot find your car, then it means that you have lost a little bit of yourself along the way toward your goals. You are turning into someone you dread or someone you don't know anymore.

context: To dream that you are getting a parking ticket
meaning: suggests that you are feeling lost and not knowing what you want to do with your life. You feel that you are being judged and criticized for the path you want to take. The dream may also be analogous to your lack of accomplishments or to the setbacks in your life.

context: To dream that you are performing a parkour move
meaning: indicates that you are not letting any obstacles stand in your way of your goals. Alternatively, the dream means that you are in tune with your surroundings and environment. You are able to adapt to any situation.

context: To see someone performing parkour in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to be more flexible and efficient with how your manage your time.

context: To dream that you are part of parliament
meaning: represents your leadership abilities. You need to speak up about some public matter. Alternatively, the dream means that you are seeking the spotlight or looking for attention.

context: To dream that you are on parole
meaning: implies that you need to consider the consequence of all your actions. There is a higher force who you need to answer to.

context: To see a parrot in your dream
meaning: represents some message or gossip that is being conveyed to you. You need to think twice about repeating or sharing certain information. Alternatively, the parrot can denote a person in your waking life who is eccentric or obnoxious. It may also mean that you or someone is being repetitive or even mocking you.

context: To see parsley in your dream
meaning: represents success. Your achievements will soon be recognized. Alternatively, it symbolizes purification. You need to rid yourself of the negativity and things that are weighing you down.

context: To see a partner in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to seek the help of others in order to accomplish a mutual goal. Alternatively, a partner symbolizes the duality of your personality. Also consider your waking relationship with your own partner.

context: To dream about partner swapping
meaning: suggests that you want to add some spice to your sex life. You want to be more sexually adventurous. Consider the couple who you are swapping with for additional significance. Alternatively, the dream may mean that there are certain aspects that you wish that your significant other possess.

context: To see a partridge in your dream
meaning: signifies independence. The partridge highlights your leadership abilities. Alternatively, it represents deception and temptation.

context: To dream that you are at a party
meaning: suggests that you need to get out more and enjoy yourself. If the party is a bad one, then it indicates that you are unsure of your social skills. If you dream that you are at your own birthday party, then it represents appreciation for the life you have.

context: To dream that you are planning a party
meaning: implies that you are being too methodical and need to be more spontaneous. It is time to let loose. Alternatively, the dream may simply reflect your stress level about planning an actual party.

context: If you are a man and dream that there are only men at a party
meaning: suggests that you are questioning your abilities. You fear that you are being overlooked or not measuring up to others. Or perhaps you are also expressing desires of blending in and not standing out.

context: Dreaming that you are having a Tupperware party
meaning: symbolizes your practical thinking.

context: To see a party horn in your dream
meaning: indicates that you do not have an outlet to freely express yourself. You feel stifled in some way.

context: To discover secret passageways in your dream
meaning: parallel to something new and/or exciting that is occurring in your waking life. It refers to a new opportunity, a new relationship, or a new attitude toward life. If you wake up before fully exploring these passageways, then it suggest that you may not know how to take advantage of these opportunities or how to move forward with a relationship. Perhaps the newness and uncertainty of this discovery also makes you a little more cautious. Overall, this is a positive dream.

context: To dream that you are a passenger
meaning: suggests that you are not in control of your life. You are letting others decide for you. To see other passengers in your dream indicates that you are spending too much energy pleasing others. Perhaps, you feel that others have been leeching off of you.

context: To see or eat a passion fruit in your dream
meaning: represents your spiritual connection. You are in tune with your spirituality. Alternatively, it signifies fertility, good health, life and longevity. The allure and invitation of sex is also implied. The dream may be a metaphor for a project (fruit) that you are "passionate" about.

context: To drink passion fruit in your dream
meaning: signifies life or vitality.

context: To see a passport in your dream
meaning: represents your identity and your ability to traverse through various situations. You are experiencing new found freedom to do what you want and go where you want. You may be going through a period of self-discovery.

context: To dream that you lose your passport
meaning: indicates that you are trying to find yourself and get a sense of who you are. Alternatively, the dream means that opportunities are closing off to you.

context: To dream that your passport is getting stamped
meaning: represents approval. You are given the green light to go ahead with a new project or journey.

context: To see a password in your dream
meaning: represents access and control. You hold the key to unlocking your inner feelings and emotions. Analyze the letters and/or numbers within the password for additional significance. It could be a hidden message.

context: To dream that you forget your password
meaning: indicates a loss of control in some aspect of your waking life.

context: To dream of the past
meaning: suggests that a current waking situation is paralleling a past situation. You need to learn from the past and not make the same mistake again. Alternatively, the dream may represent unresolved issues from the past. Or that you need to stop living in the past and look forward toward the future.

context: To dream that you have a past life
meaning: indicates greater awareness of your subconscious. You are seeking for better understand of your Self and of your origins. The past life may reflect an actual past life or it may be the life that your parents or grandparents or ancestors were living. Alternatively, the dream refers to previous lessons that you can learn from. You are open to rectifying current issues in order to move forward.

context: To make or eat pasta in your dream
meaning: represents your need for energy. Also consider the shape of the pasta and how it relates to a waking situation. Penne signifies your narrow perspective. Spaghetti noodles symbolize an entangling situation. Elbow shaped pasta represents your need to focus on yourself more. And corkscrew pasta means that some aspect of your life is out of control.

context: #Ref:glue
meaning: #Ref:glue

context: To dream of pastel colors
meaning: indicate that you are not fully recognizing and dealing with some part of your emotions. There is some ambiguity in your life.

context: To see a pastor in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are in need of spiritual guidance and advice. You may be experiencing feelings of guilt.

context: To see or eat a pastry in your dream
meaning: refers to indulgence, sensual pleasure and satisfaction. You are enjoying life and reaping its rewards.

context: To dream that you are applying for a patent
meaning: signifies your successes and your many accomplishments. It also means that you need to be more methodical in how you pursue your goals.

context: To walk through an open path in your dream
meaning: signifies clarity of thought and peace of mind. It also symbolizes your progress.

context: To see a blocked or windy path in your dream
meaning: denotes that you need to give serious attention to the direction you are heading in your personal and/or business life. You need to take time out to consider and rethink the consequences before acting on your choices.

context: To dream that you are a patient
meaning: suggests that you are going through a healing process. Alternatively, this dream may be a pun on your need for patience. Remember that good things come to those who wait.

context: To dream that you are in the patio
meaning: represents your openness toward a particular situation.

context: To dream that the doors to the patio are opened
meaning: refer to your receptive state of mind. If they are closed, then it indicates that you are not being open to a situation. Patio doors symbolize the merging of your mental and spiritual state.

context: To dream that you commit patricide
meaning: means that you are rejecting authority and rules. You refuse to answer to a higher power. Alternatively, killing your father may also be symbolic of killing an aspect of your own self. You feel that you are becoming like your father and you don't like it.

context: To see a pattern in your dream
meaning: suggests that your life has become monotonous and repetitious. You need to break free from the routine.

context: To see or work with a dress pattern in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are trying to emulate somebody. The dream may be a metaphor that you are trying to "pattern" yourself after someone you look up to. Or perhaps you are lacking your own identity.

context: To play patty-cake in your dream
meaning: represents your carefree nature. You approach life to your own rhythm and beat. Alternatively, the dream implies that you are wasting your time and energy on unproductive pursuits.

context: To see children playing patty-cake
meaning: refers to your own childhood memories. The dream may serve to remind you not to take some things too seriously.

context: To dream that you are a pauper
meaning: suggests that you are not utilizing your inner talents and full potential. You are not acknowledging your own self-worth.

context: To see or walk on pavement in your dream
meaning: suggests that you have a clear understanding and grasp of a situation. You are standing on solid ground. The dream may also indicate that you have paved and laid out a firm path toward your life goals.

context: To see an animal paw in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to trust your intuition and animal instincts. The dream may also be a pun on your "Pa" or father.

context: To see bloody paw prints in your dream
meaning: represents a repression of your animalistic desires.

context: To see or be in a pawnshop in your dream
