context: To dream that you are getting your ears pierced
meaning: represents some stinging remarks or insults.

context: To dream that you or someone has a nose piercing
meaning: implies that you need to pay closer attention to some issue. Focus!

context: Less symbolically, dreams of getting pierced
meaning: may just be your waking desire or anxiety on getting pierced.

context: To see the pieta in your dream
meaning: symbolizes the eternal bond and love between mother and child. The dream also points to a mother's loss. This loss does not necessarily mean death, but rather an end to something.

context: To see a pig in your dream
meaning: symbolizes dirtiness, greediness, stubbornness or selfishness. Alternatively, the pig may represent gluttony, opulence and overindulgence. Perhaps it refers to someone who is dirty or someone who is chauvinistic.

context: If you like pigs and think that pigs are cute,
meaning: then your dream about a fat dirty pig represents your misconceptions about certain things. What you believe and what is reality may be two different things. This pig may be analogous to a relationship or a man in your life. You think that the pig will be a certain way, but in actuality reality is not at all what you had imagined.

context: To see a pig being cooked alive in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are undergoing a drastic transformation. You are ready to rid yourself of the negativity surrounding your life.

context: To see a pigeon in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are taking the blame for the actions of others. Pigeons also represent gossip or news. Perhaps the pigeon refers to a message from your subconscious. Alternatively, the dream may be expressing a desire to return home.

context: To dream that a pigeon is being eaten or swallowed by another animal
meaning: implies that you will suffer the consequences of spreading some rumor or news.

context: To dream that you are giving someone a piggyback ride
meaning: symbolizes your supportive role. You literally feel that you are carrying the weight of others. Perhaps you are feeling overwhelmed of being the responsible or dependent one.

context: To dream that you are riding piggyback on someone
meaning: represents your lack of power or control in a situation. You are just going along with whatever decisions are being made. Alternatively, being on piggyback points to issues of codependency.

context: To see a piggybank in your dream
meaning: represents financial worries. Perhaps you need to cut back on your spending or adhere to a budget.

context: To see a piglet in your dream
meaning: refers to someone in your life who has character flaws and imperfections, but you accept them. That someone may even be yourself. Alternatively, piglets are also symbolic of children.

context: To see a pigsty in your dream
meaning: symbolizes a messy situation. The dream is making a commentary on your waking life. You need to organize and sort out some life issues so you can progress forward. Alternatively, the dream indicates an attack on your character.

context: To dream that you are wearing pigtails
meaning: indicates a regression into childhood, where times were more innocent and carefree. You are displaying a "don't-care" attitude and don't want to be weighed down by responsibilities.

context: To see a pile of something in your dream
meaning: signifies some overwhelming burden or excess in your life. In particular, to see a pile of papers in your dream represents your overwhelming responsibilities and stresses that you are having to cope with. You are not effectively dealing with the issues at hand.

context: To see a pile of debris or trash in your dream
meaning: represents the rejected or unwanted aspects of yourself. To see a pile of wood in your dream symbolizes your overwhelming passion.

context: To dream that you are a pilgrim
meaning: suggests that you are undergoing a spiritual journey.

context: To see a pilgrim in your dream
meaning: represents an aspect of yourself that is striving toward greater understanding of who you are and of the world you live in.

context: To see or take a pill in your dream
meaning: signifies a restoration of your inner harmony. You are experiencing a period of healing and an end to the negative ideas in your mind. Alternatively, the dream may be a metaphor for something or someone who is hard to follow.

context: To see a pillar in your dream
meaning: represents your strength, stability, and a firm stance, especially in the face of adversity. Alternatively, the dream indicates that you have the full support of those around you. You are being honored and recognized. As with most elongate objects, a pillar may also have phallic connotations.

context: To see a pillow in your dream
meaning: represents comfort. relaxation, ease, and/or luxury. You need to take it easy on yourself. Alternatively, the dream indicates laziness. If the pillow is lumpy, then it indicates that there is something unsettling in your mind.

context: To dream that you are lying on a pillow
meaning: suggests that you are in need of some mental support. Perhaps there is a situation or matter that you need to "cushion" and soften the blow.

context: To dream that your pillow is gone
meaning: indicates that you are in self-denial.

context: To dream that you are a pilot
meaning: indicates that you are in complete control of your destination in life. You are confident and self-assured in your decisions and accomplishments.

context: To dream that you have a pimple
meaning: relates to issues about your self-esteem and self-image. You are feeling awkward or out of place in some situation or relationship.

context: To dream that you are popping a pimple
meaning: indicates that some negative emotion needs to be expressed and acknowledge. These emotions that you are holding back are on the verge of erupting.

context: To dream that you are pricked by a pin
meaning: signifies a sticky situation or relationship that is falling apart or that is unstable. You may be feeling anxious or feeling the need to hold together a particular relationship. Also consider the dream as a metaphor for someone who may be a "prick".
Alternatively, to see pins in your dream refer to feeling of being trapped or immobilized, as exemplified by the phrase "being pinned down".

context: To see or use a pin cushion in your dream
meaning: signifies stinging remarks or hurtful comments. You are feeling used and manipulated. Alternatively, a pin cushion means that you are trying to harm others with your sharp words and negative attitude.

context: To see a piata in your dream
meaning: symbolizes joy, celebration and festivities. If you smashed open the piata, then it suggests that you will be well rewarded for your tenacity, drive and hard work. If you are unable to hit the piata, then it indicates that you are experiencing difficulties toward success, even though it may be seemingly within reach. Perhaps you have a self-defeatist attitude. You need to believe in yourself and in your abilities.

context: To dream that insects are inside the piata
meaning: indicates that you have been mislead. Perhaps someone in your life has not delivered on their promise. The dream could also be telling you that some offer may be too good to be true. Don't take it!

context: To see a pinball machine or dream that you are playing pinball
meaning: suggests that with patience, control, and precision, you will succeed in your goals. Something that may look risky or challenging at first can be tackled if you break it down.

context: To see or play with a pinwheel in your dream
meaning: suggests that you will succeed on your own power and your creative energy. Alternatively, a pinwheel symbolizes childhood and your carefree nature. Consider the color(s) of the pinwheel.

context: To dream that you have pincers for hands
meaning: suggest that you are going to great lengths to try to get your hands on something, even through underhanded means.

context: To see or be grabbed by pincers in your dream
meaning: indicates that someone or some situation has a strong hold over you. Perhaps they have something on you.

context: To dream that someone is pinching you
meaning: suggests that you need a reality check. Perhaps your goals or ideals are too lofty. Alternatively, the dream indicates that things are going smoothly for you. You may even feel that something is too good to be true.

context: To see a pine tree in your dream
meaning: symbolizes immortality, life, and/or fertility. The dream could also be a pun on "pining" for something or someone.

context: To smell pine in your dream
meaning: indicates that you need to be reenergized and uplifted.

context: To see a pineapple in your dream
meaning: represents self-confidence, ambition and success. You are self-assured in what you do. Alternatively, the pineapples symbolize hospitality. Or perhaps you need to relax or take a vacation.

context: To eat a pineapple
meaning: indicates sexual problems and issues of losing control.

context: To see a pinecone in your dream
meaning: symbolizes wealth and good fortune. Alternatively, a pinecone represents life and fertility. The dream could also be a pun on "pining" for something or someone.

context: To see or play ping pong in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are going back and forth between two choices. You are confused over an important decision in your life and have difficulty committing to a decision, to a relationship or social obligation.

context: To notice your pinky finger in your dream
meaning: represents mental power, intellect, memory, and the power of communication.

context: To see Pinocchio in your dream
meaning: suggests that you or someone are not being truthful in some situation.

context: To dream that you are a pioneer
meaning: suggests that you are exploring aspects of your subconscious. You are looking for a new way to express yourself and expand your thinking.

context: To see a water pipe in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are open and receptive to new ideas. It may also represent your connections to those around you. You are able to steer something toward a direction.

context: To dream that you are inside a pipe
meaning: represents your narrow vision and your seemingly lack of options. Perhaps the dream is telling you to look at things from a different angle.

context: To dream that you are smoking a pipe
meaning: denotes knowledge or contemplation. Alternatively, it symbolizes comfort, relaxation, contentment and satisfaction with your waking life. If someone in your life smokes a pipe, then the dream symbol may serve as a reminder of her or him.

context: To see piranhas in your dream
meaning: suggest that something is eating away at your subconscious. You need to release some of those pent up feelings and confront those issues that are causing much internal conflict.

context: To see a pirate in your dream
meaning: signifies that some person or situation is adding chaos to your emotional life. You feel that someone has violated your integrity or creativity. Alternatively, the pirate may symbolize freedom, risk, and adventure. You want to explore new adventures and take riskier ventures.

context: To dream that you are a pirate
meaning: suggests that you are taking advantage of others. The dream may be a metaphor that you are "pirating" something and taking something that does not rightfully belong to you.

context: To see a pirate ship in your dream
meaning: signifies your suppressed desires for freedom and adventure. You want to cut loose and go wild. Alternatively, the dream symbolizes hidden danger or hostility.

context: To dream of a flying pirate ship
meaning: implies that you are letting your adventurous side guide you and take control. You are living it up!

context: To dream that you are doing pirouettes
meaning: represents your ability to balance many responsibilities at the same time. You have total control over your life. Alternatively, the dream highlights your grace and poise in a situation or circumstance.

context: To dream that someone is a Pisces
meaning: indicates your sensitivity, imagination, compassion and sympathy for others. It suggests that you are ready to make certain sacrifices for what you believe in. Alternatively, the dream may reflect your inability to change who you are.

context: #Ref:urination
meaning: #Ref:urination

context: To see a pistachio in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are ready to explore and open yourself to new experiences. What you thought was difficult at first is going to be worth your while. Alternatively, dreaming of eating pistachios symbolizes joy and positivity.

context: To dream that you are aiming a pistol
meaning: denotes that you are trying to target a specific goal. Alternatively, the dream also symbolizes fear, anger and aggression. You are using your power to defend yourself against the fear and anger. It may also indicate your hot and quick temper.

context: To see a piston in your dream
meaning: symbolizes your drive, determination and ambition. You are evaluating your goals and your means to achieve them. Alternatively, the dream may also be a metaphor for sexual activity. You may be lacking passion in your sex life to the point where it has gotten somewhat mechanical.

context: To dream that you are in a pit
meaning: indicates feelings of hopelessness about some situation or circumstance. Also consider the familiar phrase of "being in the pits".

context: If you dream that you are falling into a bottomless pit,
meaning: then it suggests that you are unable to recover from a setback or that you are unable to overcome some problem.

context: To see a pit bull in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are on the defensive. You may be feeling threatened.

context: To dream that you own a pit bull
meaning: indicates that you are well protected or perhaps even overly protective.

context: To see or eat pita in your dream
meaning: represents wholeness and the circle of life. It refers to the positive things and sacrifices you have made in your life. Alternatively, pita symbolizes the womb.

context: To see a water pitcher in your dream
meaning: refers to the outpouring of ideas, knowledge, or emotions. You may be spilling your guts out to others and sharing aspects of yourself which you have previously kept to yourself.

context: To see a baseball pitcher in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are in control. You have the power to make decisions and change the course that you are taking.

context: To see a pitchfork in your dream
meaning: symbolizes self-sufficiency. You need to learn to do things for yourself. Alternatively, the dream suggests that you are seeking a simpler way of life.

context: To have a dream where the images are pixelated
meaning: indicates a lack of clarity in a situation. Alternatively, if you see pixels of a picture, then it means that you are too focused on small details. You need to look at the big picture.

context: To see a pixie in your dream
meaning: indicates your childish ways. It may also represent your unrecognized energy and your hidden potential. Alternatively, the dream means that you need to seek some outside advice.

context: To dream that you are in a pizzeria
meaning: implies that you are surrounded by love and warmth. You feel at ease.

context: Dreaming that your own a pizzeria
meaning: represents dedication and commitment.

context: To see or put a place mat on a table in your dream
meaning: represents where you stand in your personal relationship. You may be entering into a new relationship, either on a friendship level or romantic level. Alternatively, the dream signifies your sociability, your openness and your sharing nature.

context: To see a placenta in your dream
meaning: symbolizes dependency and reliance on other people. It also suggests that there is something in your life that is no longer needed. You need to let go of some unnecessary burden.

context: Places
meaning: To dream of a certain place in your dream is telling of your inner state of mind. Consider the feel, the appearance, and the coloring of the place. Also consider your own personal feelings and memories with that particular place.

context: To dream of a plague
meaning: indicates that you are being confronted with a broad issue that affects those around you. The decisions that you make will have a major impact and large-scale consequences.

context: To dream that you are wearing plaid
meaning: suggests that some of your conservative views are in conflict with your liberal and wild side.

context: To see the plains in your dream
meaning: represent wholesomeness and homegrown goodness. Alternatively, the dream suggests that you have a clear and smooth path ahead. The plains may also be a pun on someone who is plain.

context: To dream that you are planning an activity or event
meaning: indicates that you need to be more organized and methodical in your decision-making and other aspects of your daily life. There are some issues that you are trying to sort out. Alternatively, the dream may reflect your actual stress or concerns about the activity or event in real life.

context: Plan
meaning: Dreams can help you solve certain problems that you are stuck on. The solution to a problem came about in a dream for some inventors and scientists. Some authors look to their dreams for their novels. Thus dreaming of a plan may give you an answer to a problem you are having.

context: If you dream of having plans or making plans,
meaning: then it means that you need to make a commitment and stick to it.

context: To see a plane in your dream
meaning: may be a pun on someone or something that is "plain". Perhaps the plane refers to a new level.

context: To see a planet in your dream
meaning: signifies creativity, exploration, and new adventures. You are trying to align yourself with untapped energies that you never knew you had. Alternatively, to dream of planets, suggests that you are trying to escape from your own waking reality.

context: To dream that you discover life on a new planet
meaning: refers to your desire to escape from a current situation. Alternatively, the dream represents your own self-discovery. You have uncovered a part of yourself that you did not realize existed within yourself.

context: Planet
meaning: Look up the specific planet for additional significance.

context: To dream that you are walking the plank
meaning: suggests you are feeling emotionally vulnerable. You are plunging into new emotional territory.

context: To see a wooden plank
meaning: indicates something that is in need of repair or that you need to maximize your resources and make something out of seemingly nothing.

context: To dream that you are planting something
meaning: represents your faith and optimism about the future. You have an optimistic view.

context: To see plants in your dream
meaning: indicate fertility, spiritual development, potential, and growth. Alternatively, the appearance of plants in your dream reflect your caring and loving nature. If you are estranged from your children, then the plants may be seen as representative for your children.

context: In particular, to see indoor plants in your dream
meaning: suggest that your growth is being hindered or slowed in some way. You are experiencing a lack of independence. Alternatively, the dream signifies your desire to be closer to nature.

context: To see droopy, withered or dead plants in your dream
meaning: suggest that you are at a standstill in your life. You are lacking initiative.

context: Dreaming that plants are growing at a rapid pace or that the plants are growing right before your eyes
meaning: mean that time is passing you by. You are taking certain things for granted or that you are not taking the time to notice the little things in life.

context: To work with plaster in your dream
meaning: suggests that there is some matter that you are trying to resolve or settle.

context: If you are making a plaster mold in your dream,
meaning: then it means that you are stuck with living in the past. You are unwilling to change and evolve with the times.

context: To see plastic objects in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are being fake, artificial and/or insensitive in some way. You are not being genuine and true to yourself. Alternatively, it signifies flexibility in your way of thinking.

context: To see or use a plastic bag in your dream
meaning: represents the temporary burdens and responsibilities that you are carrying with you. You need to exercise better control in certain areas of your life. Alternatively, it denotes concern for the environment.

context: To dream that you are having plastic surgery
meaning: suggests that you are rebuilding your self-esteem and trying to improve your self-image. The dream may be an anxiety dream if you are considering plastic surgery or scheduled to go in for plastic surgery.

context: To see a plate in your dream
meaning: symbolizes your hunger for life. You are showing potential and promise for the future. The dream may be a symbol that you have too much on your plate.

context: If the plate is empty in your dream,
meaning: then it indicates that there is an emotional void in your waking life. You may be feeling left out. Alternatively, it suggests that you need to rethink your priorities.

context: To dream that you are on a plateau
meaning: suggests that you are in a rut. You feel that your life is going nowhere or that you are lacking excitement in your life. Perhaps you are just taking a breather from life's fast pace. Alternatively, the plateau symbolizes a high state of consciousness.

context: To see or wear platform shoes in your dream
meaning: indicate that you need to stand tall and be proud. You are striving for a higher status in life. Alternatively, the dream may be a pun on having a "platform" on some political position. Due to its association with the seventies, the dream indicate the easy going and party attitudes of that era.

context: To see platinum in your dream
meaning: symbolizes success, prosperity and wealth. Your achievements and accomplishments are attributed to your determination and drive. Do not ever believe that your goals are unattainable. Alternatively, the platinum represents coldness and toughness to your exterior persona.

context: To see a platter in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are feeling lazy or envious. Alternatively, the dream refers to some sort of entitlement. Perhaps you are wanting everything served to you "on a silver platter".

context: To see a platypus in your dream
meaning: refers to your tendency to wallow and dwell on your emotions. It may also suggest that your repressed thoughts and subconscious materials are slowly coming to the surface and making its presence known. Alternatively, a platypus is indicative of shyness and reservation, especially in social situations.

context: To dream that you are playing
meaning: refers to your tendency to go against the norm and break the rules of convention. You are displaying unrestricted creativity. Alternatively, playing implies that you are all work and no play. You need to relax and let loose. On the other hand, the dream may also be saying that you are not taking things seriously enough. You need to face reality.

context: To dream that you are in a play
meaning: represents the roles you play in your life and the various acts and personas you put on. If you are watching the play, then it suggests that you need to draw from the inspiration of others.

context: To dream that you are playing with Play Doh
meaning: refers to your ability to create something from an idea. You are using your imagination and exploring possibilities. Alternatively, dreaming about Play Doh signifies something that you are trying to manipulate.

context: To dream that you are on a playground
meaning: indicates your desires to escape from your daily responsibilities. Perhaps you need to be more carefree. You need to acknowledge your talents.

context: To see a playpen in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to make time for leisure and pleasure. Alternatively, the dream refers to your immature actions and behavior.

context: To see a pair of pliers in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to draw out all the details of a situation before you make a decision about it. Alternatively, the dream means that you need to rid yourself of something from your life.

meaning: #Ref:conspiracy

context: To see a plough in your dream
meaning: represents growth and expansion. You are cultivating new ideas and projects.

context: To dream that you are plowing
meaning: indicates that you are making a fresh new start. You are preparing yourself for growth and change. Alternatively, the dream may represent the monotony or routine of your daily life.

context: To see a plug in your dream
meaning: represents power, potential and untapped energies. You need to draw from within in order to move forward. Alternatively, the dream may be a pun that you need to stay "plugged in" about some information or news. There is something that you need to be aware of.

context: To see or eat a plum in your dream
meaning: symbolizes youth and vitality. The plum may also represent you self-image and the way you feel about your body. Perhaps the dream is a pun on being "plump".

context: To see a plum tree in your dream
meaning: represents youth, vitality, and innocence. The dream also indicates that you will overcome some difficulties.

context: To notice plumage in your dream
meaning: signifies a need to feel protected and shielded from the elements. It also symbolizes an outward display of strength, triumph and power. You are being a little show-offy.

context: To see a plumber in your dream
meaning: suggests that there is some emotional issue that you need to deal with instead of letting it clog up within you. Perhaps you need to turn to a friend or even professional help in order to deal with your problems effectively.

context: To see plumbing in your dream
meaning: symbolizes the flow of emotions. If the plumbing is clogged up, then it signifies repressed or pent up emotions that needs to be released and expressed. Seeing plumbing may also be a metaphor for your body and its internal working. Thus the dream may point to health concerns.

context: To dream that you are plunging into something
meaning: indicates that you are facing some uncertainty in your waking life. You need to be willing to take a risk in order to move forward toward your goals.

context: To dream that something is plunging in your chest or someone else's chest
meaning: suggests that you are ignoring some obvious truth. You are refusing to acknowledge and confront the truth.

symbol: To see a plunger in your dream suggests that you need to force yourself to confront certain emotions. It is hindering your progress and preventing you from moving forward in your life.Pluto
context: To see Pluto in your dream
meaning: symbolizes death and destruction. You are undergoing a rebirth an a transformation. Your hidden potential will also be unveiled.

context: To see plywood in your dream
meaning: represents flexibility and creativity in your way of thinking. Alternatively, it also symbolizes warmth.

context: To see a pocket in your dream
meaning: represents your hidden talents and undeveloped abilities. You are not utilizing your strengths to the fullest potential. Did you find anything in the pocket? Consider the significance of what is inside the pocket. If the pocket is empty, then it symbolizes the womb and your desire to isolate yourself from others. Alternatively, a pocket symbolizes secrets. If there is a hole in the pocket, then it implies that your resources or abilities are being drained.

context: To see or wear a pocket watch in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are too overly concerned with time. You are being chained down by time. Be more spontaneous. Alternatively, the dream represents your old fashioned thinking and outdated attitude. You are living in the old ages. The pocket watch may also symbolize the ticking of the human heart and thus is indicative of the emotional side of your life.

context: To see a pocketknife in your dream
meaning: suggests a good friend is hiding her or his true feelings.

context: To dream that you are standing at a podium
meaning: suggests that there is something important that you need to say and get out. You need to be heard. Perhaps you are having difficulties conveying your message and it is weighing on your mind. Just let it out! Alternatively, dream that you are at a podium denotes your position of prominence and status. You are an influential figure.

context: To see or read poetry in your dream
meaning: signifies inspiration and idealistic notions. It also suggests that you need to improve the lines of communications with someone.

context: To see or play with a pogo stick in your dream
meaning: represents life's ups and downs. If you do not have control of your pogo stick, then it indicates that you are all over the place in your emotions and thinking. You need to focus and zero in on one issue at a time. Alternatively, being on a pogo stick may be analogous to sex.

context: To see poinsettias in your dream
meaning: symbolize joy, good health and/or festivity. The dream may also imply that you need an uplift to your spirit.

context: To see something pointed in your dream
meaning: represents action, urgency and completion. The dream suggests that you have arrived to a decision or common understanding. Alternatively, the dream may also be a metaphor that there is a point to your dream. Or you need to get your point across.

context: To dream that you are pointing at someone or something
meaning: indicates that you need to pay more attention to that particular person or object. The dream may be showing you the way to solving a problem in your waking life.

context: To dream someone is pointing at you
meaning: suggests feelings of self guilt or even shame. You are being accused of some wrongdoing.

context: To see poison in your dream
meaning: denotes that you need to get rid of something in your life that is causing you much sickness and distress. You need to cleanse and purge away the negativity in your life.

context: To dream that you ingest or inhale poison
meaning: indicates that you are introducing something into yourself that is harmful to your well-being. This may be feelings of bitterness, jealousy or other negative feelings that are consuming you.

context: To see poison ivy in your dream
meaning: refers to your vengeful or devious thoughts. It is indicative of resentment, jealousy, and revenge. Alternatively, poison ivy represents a situation, behavior or condition that you need to avoid. Perhaps you need to avoid certain food, habit, person, situation, etc.

context: To dream that you are being poked
meaning: represents something that needs your attention. Perhaps the dream is giving you a poke or a nudge to move forward. Thus, the dream may be a pun on being "pokey" or slow. You need to stop sitting around and start accomplishing your goals.

context: To play pokemon in your dream
meaning: indicates a desire to expand your social circle. You are looking for acceptance.

context: To dream that you are a pokemon
meaning: points to your individualism and qualities that sets your apart from others.

context: To dream that you are playing poker
meaning: suggests that a situation in your waking life requires strategy and careful planning. You need to think things through before carrying out your actions. Alternatively, the dream may also be a pun on "poke her". Are you trying to get a girl's attention?

context: To see poker chips in your dream
meaning: symbolize the uncertainty of life. Sometimes you need to take a chance.

context: To see a polar bear in your dream
meaning: signifies a reawakening. Alternatively, the polar bear symbolizes your frigid and cold emotions.

context: To see a pole in your dream
meaning: represents security and stability. The dream is a reminder that you always have something or someone you can lean on. Alternatively, the dream may also be a phallic symbol.

context: To dream that you are pole dancing
meaning: symbolizes your sexual expression. You need to be more open and expressive with your sexuality. The pole is a phallic symbol. Thus the dream may be analogous to some that you have wrapped around your finger.

context: To dream that you are pole vaulting
meaning: indicates that you are trying to overcome some sexual issue.

context: To see the police in your dream
meaning: symbolizes structure, rules, power, authority and control. You need to put an end to your reckless behavior or else the law will catch up to you. Alternatively, the dream refers to failure in honoring your obligation and commitments.

context: To dream that you are arrested by the police
meaning: suggests that you feel sexually or emotionally restrained because of guilt. The dream may also be a metaphor that you are feeling apprehensive about something.

context: To dream that you are a police officer
meaning: represents your own sense of morality and conscience. The dream may serve to guide you down a straight path. If you have recurring dreams that you are a police officer, then it may mean that your past actions are leaving you with guilt. Consider your behavior and actions as the cop. If your dream that you are in pursuit of a suspect, then it indicates that your naughty and devious side is in conflict with your moral standards. To dream that you are an undercover cop implies that you are going against your conscience.

context: To dream that you are having difficulties contacting the police
meaning: suggests that you have yet to acknowledge your own authoritativeness in a situation. You need to take control and be in command of the direction of your life.

context: To dream that you are pulled over by the police
meaning: suggests that you need to slow down and take things down a notch.

context: Dreaming that you are running from the police
meaning: means that you are refusing to face the consequences of your actions. It also indicates that you are rejecting certain rules.

context: To see a police car in your dream
meaning: indicates that help is on the way for you. You are experiencing some inner turmoil and need intervention.

context: To dream of a political party
meaning: suggests that you need to stand up and defend your beliefs. Be prepared for any dissent and backlash.

context: To see police tape in your dream
meaning: represents protection from your subconscious. Something is preventing you from delving deeper. Alternatively, the dream symbolizes restriction.

context: To dream that you are polishing metal
meaning: means that you are honing your skills and realizing your full potential.

context: If you dream that you are polishing rocks or stones,
meaning: then it indicates that you are able to see the true beauty in something or someone. It represents endurance, patience and longevity.

context: To dream that you are a politician
meaning: indicates that you are being deceptive and manipulative. Alternatively, the dream suggests that you are trying to persuade others to support your views and ideas. Perhaps you are abusing your position in some situation in your life.

context: To see a politician in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to choose and take a side. The dream parallels a decision that you need to make in your waking life. Alternatively, the politician may reflect your desires for political office or your interest in world affairs.

context: To see polka dots in your dream
meaning: symbolize routine and monotony. If the polka dots are misshapen, then it refers to your desire to break out of the routine; you want a change of pace.

context: To see or dream that you are at a poll booth
meaning: represents your desires to make a difference in your community or society. You want to leave an impact on others. Alternatively, the dream indicates that you are feeling boxed in or cornered.

context: To see or inhale pollen in your dream
meaning: represents the annoyances in your life. You are feeling irritable. Alternatively, it signifies the sharing and spreading of new ideas.

context: To dream of pollution

In the second trimester, dreams will reflect anxieties about being a good mother and concerns about possible complications with the birth. Dreams of giving birth to a non-human baby are also common during this period of the pregnancy. Finally, in the third trimester, dreams consists of labor, being attacked or something happening to the baby. As your body changes and grows, dreams of whales, elephants and dinosaurs and other larger animals may also start appearing at this stage of pregnancy.

Alternatively, a prostate exam indicates that you are uptight about something. A more direct interpretation of this dream may be that you are nervous about an upcoming prostate exam.

context: To dream that you have a prosthesis
meaning: indicates that you are exploring a new perspective in life. You are reaching out in a different and profound way. Consider also where on the body the prosthesis is fitted as that body part may offer additional significance. If you have a prosthetic arm, then it means that you are exploring a completely new way of doing something. If you have a prosthetic leg, then it means that you are headed toward a new journey.

context: To dream that you are a prostitute
meaning: indicates your desires for more sexual freedom/expression and sexual power. You want to be less inhibited and explore other areas of sexuality. Perhaps your waking ideology about sex is too rigid. On a negative side, to dream that you are a prostitute suggests that you are harboring feelings of guilt toward a relationship. You are having difficulties integrating love and sexuality. Alternatively, the dream may be a metaphor suggesting that you are "prostituting" yourself in some situation, either emotionally or morally. Are you selling yourself in some way?

context: To see or dream that you are with a prostitute
meaning: suggests that you are feeling sexually deprived or needy. Alternatively, the dream is commenting on how you wished that sexual relationships were more simple and straightforward.

context: To dream that you are being protected or need protection
meaning: indicates that you are feeling helpless in some situation. Life's difficulties has made you dependable on others. You need to start taking charge of the situation.

context: To dream that you are protecting someone or something
meaning: suggests that you are putting up an emotional wall or barrier between you and others around you. Consider who or what you are protecting for clues as to what aspect of your own self you are afraid of letting out and letting others know.

context: To dream that you are at a protest
meaning: indicates that you need to speak up for yourself and for your rights. Pay attention to the details of your dream as you may be ignoring or overlooking some important issue in your life. It is time to take action.

context: To see or use a protractor in your dream
meaning: implies that you are trying to look at things from someone else's angle. You want to put yourself in their place so you can better relate to what they are going through or experiencing. Alternatively, the dream may be a pun; you are looking for a time extension on something.

context: #Ref:intruder
meaning: #Ref:intruder

context: To dream that you are pruning
meaning: represents growth. You need to get rid and cut away at your old habits and former ways in order to move forward. Get rid of what you no longer need.

context: To see prunes in your dream
meaning: symbolize an emotional or creative blockage. It may also imply old age as suggested by the metaphor "as wrinkled as a prune".

context: #Ref:crowbar
meaning: #Ref:crowbar

context: To see a psychic in your dream
meaning: represents your desires to know the unknown. You are experiencing anxieties about the future and in achieving your goals. Additionally, you may feel a lack of control in the path that your life is taking.

context: To dream that you are psychic
meaning: represents your intuition and the sensitive side of your personality.

context: To dream that you have psychokinesis
meaning: indicates how you manipulate your surroundings. You are being over controlling.

context: To see or dream that you are a psychologist
meaning: symbolizes the intellectual and mental aspect of yourself. Perhaps you to be more understanding about a situation or event. Don't be so hard on yourself.

context: To see a psychopath in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are being deceived or manipulated. It may also mean that you are feeling detached.

context: To dream that you are a psychopath
meaning: implies that you are feeling larger than life. The dream is a warning that your ego is getting out of control.

context: To see a pterodactyl in your dream
meaning: implies that your sexual desires are reaching new heights. Alternatively, the dream refers to a conflict between your primal urges and your rational mind.

context: To dream that you are in a pub
meaning: represents your social interactions and how you relate to others. Sometimes you need to relax and let loose sometimes.

context: To see pubic hair in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are coyly making your sexual feelings known.

context: To dream that you are speaking in public
meaning: indicates that you need to vocalize your feelings and thoughts. You need to communicate something important and/or urgent. Alternatively, the dream may highlight your fear and nervousness of speaking in public, especially if you have an upcoming speech to give. Consider the demeanor and behavior of the audience. Perhaps you are afraid of being scrutinized for your actions or being judged by others. It is also a form of an anxiety dream where you are feeling exposed or put on the spot.

context: To dream that there is no one listening to your speech
meaning: suggests that you are not being acknowledged for your work or achievement. Perhaps you are feeling ignored or neglected.

context: To hear someone speaking in public in your dream
meaning: suggests that your inner feelings are being made known to those around you. Consider what is said in the speech. If you hear a politician give a speech, then it represents egotism or deceit.

context: To see or eat pudding in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are feeling slow and lethargic in your waking life. You need to be more active. Alternatively, the dream may be telling you that "the proof is in the pudding." You need to learn to question everything. Don't believe everything until you have seen it or experienced it yourself.

context: To see a puddle in your dream
meaning: represents feelings that have been downplayed and overlooked. Although these feelings may appear minor, it is worthwhile to address them before it erupts unexpectedly.

context: To see a puffer fish in your dream
meaning: signifies suppressed or unexpressed anger. You are holding something in that is on the verge of erupting at any moment. Alternatively, the dream indicates that others tend to underestimate your abilities or misjudge you.

context: To see a puffin in your dream
meaning: refers to your ability to dig into your subconscious and learn from it. You are looking within yourself for answers. It is a time for exploration, self-reflection and introspection. Perhaps you need to get to the bottom of some situation. Alternatively, a puffin may be a pun and imply your smoking habit. Or it may suggest that you are experiencing some anxiety, tension, or fear concerning a new situation in your waking life.

context: To see a pug in your dream
meaning: highlights your playful and strong character. It may also mean that you are open and receptive to new changes.

context: To do pull ups in your dream
meaning: means that you will rise above a difficult situation through your own willpower and perseverance. Alternatively, the dream suggests that you need to literally pick yourself up and move on from the past. You need to look to the future.

context: To dream that you are pulling something
meaning: refers to your burdens and struggles. You have difficulties accomplishing your tasks and goals. You need to unload and/or let go some of your responsibilities. Perhaps it is a relationship that you need to let go of. Consider also what or who you are pulling. Alternatively, the dream may be a pun on your "pull" or influence for some favor or decision.

context: To feel your pulse in your dream
meaning: symbolizes some sort of anxiety in your waking life.

context: To dream that you are feeling someone else's pulse
meaning: suggests that you are trying to connect with an aspect of that person. Perhaps you are trying to incorporate that aspect into your own self.

context: #Ref:vomiting
meaning: #Ref:vomiting

context: To see a puma in your dream
meaning: symbolizes lurking danger, aggression, raw emotions or sometimes death. You need to keep your attitude and emotions in check. Alternatively, the puma represents power, confidence, beauty and/or grace.

context: To see a pump in your dream
meaning: symbolizes untapped energy or health issues. Alternatively, it may be analogous to the heart and issues of the heart. If the pump is not working, then it signifies setbacks. Some aspects of your life is deviating from the norm.

context: To see a pumpjack in your dream
meaning: implies that you are mindlessly agreeing to things and going along with everything without questioning it. Alternatively, the dream may be telling you to say "yes" to some question you have been asking yourself.

context: To see a pumpkin in your dream
meaning: implies your openness and your receptiveness to new ideas and experiences. A pumpkin is also symbolic of female sexuality. Alternatively, the dream may relate to the popular fairy tale of Cinderella where a carriage turns back into a pumpkin. In this regard, a pumpkin may represent some situation in which time is running out.

context: To dream that you are punching someone or something
meaning: represents hidden anger and aggression. It may also be a symbol of power and your ability to draw strength from within yourself. If someone is punching you, then the dream is highlighting your helplessness and powerlessness in some waking situation. It also implies that someone is forcing their views on you. In particular, to dream that you are punched in the stomach indicates that you are experiencing some sort of emotional void.

context: To dream that you are unable to throw a punch
meaning: indicates that you are feeling helpless. You may have self-esteem and confidence issues. The dream may also be due to REM paralysis.

context: To dream that you are drinking punch
meaning: represents vitality and renewal.

context: To see or hit a punching bag in your dream
meaning: represents your pent up anger and hidden aggression. You are looking for a safe outlet to express your frustrations. Consider who or what the punch bag symbolizes. Alternatively, the dream may mean that you are feeling like a punching bag. It denotes self-punishment and self-blame.

context: To dream that you are punished
meaning: signifies guilt or shame about your actions. You need to learn to forgive yourself. Are you punishing yourself?

context: To dream that you are punishing others
meaning: signifies hidden resentment towards that person. Alternatively, they may represent aspects of your own personality that you fear or that you are trying to repress.

context: To see or dream that you are a punk
meaning: indicates rebellion. You are going against the norm and are expressing your own personal choice and freedom.

context: To dream that your pupils are red
meaning: symbolize energy, power, and vigor. Negatively, it also suggests that some negative or evil force has taken over you. A switch has been turned on inside you where you are not acting like yourself.

context: To see a puppet in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are easily swayed by others and are allowing them to control you. You feel you can not stand up for yourself.

context: To dream that you are a puppeteer
meaning: refers to your tendency to control or manipulate someone or some situation.

context: To see a puppy in your dream
meaning: symbolizes your playfulness and carefree nature. It also refers to a blossoming friendship. If you are taking care of a puppy, then it means that you are reliable and trustworthy. Others can depend on you, especially during difficult times.

context: To see a litter of newborn puppies in your dream
meaning: is indicative of the amount of time that an idea has been developing or will take to develop. Look to the number of puppies to give you that approximate amount of time.

context: To dream that you are saving a puppy
meaning: means that you are looking to recapture a more playful or carefree side of your persona.

context: #Ref:buying
meaning: #Ref:buying

context: To hear a purr in your dream
meaning: signifies satisfaction, contentment and comfort in your life. Things are going well for you. The dream may also be a pun on being "pure".

context: To see or carry a purse in your dream
meaning: represents secrets, desires and thoughts which are being closely held and guarded. It symbolizes your identity and sense of self. Consider also the condition of the purse for indications of your state of mind and feelings. Alternatively, a purse symbolizes the female genitalia and the womb.

context: To dream that you lost your purse
meaning: denotes loss of power and control. You may have lost touch with your real identity. To dream that you lost your purse, but find the contents inside means that what is inside is what matters most and what is important. You need to look past the exterior and focus on the inside. If you find a purse, then it represents a renewed sense of self.

context: To see an empty purse
meaning: represents feelings of insecurity or vulnerability.

context: To dream that someone gives your a new purse
meaning: implies that some fortune or good luck will come your way. Alternatively, a new purse is analogous to a new start. It is time to reinvent yourself and get a fresh outlook in life.

context: To dream that someone or something is in pursuit of you
meaning: indicates that you are refusing to acknowledge a certain viewpoint or idea.

context: To dream that you are in pursuit of someone or something
meaning: suggests that you are being denied of your power and influence. You need to re-evaluate your strengths and concentrate your efforts in something more worthwhile.

context: To see pus in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to express some aspect of your feeling. You may be harboring some prejudices, attitudes, or some other negative emotion that attempting to be released. You need to acknowledge these feelings and deal with them. Also consider the symbolism of where on the body the pus is located.

context: To dream that you are pushing something
meaning: symbolizes energy, effort, encouragement and motivation. You have a new drive to succeed in life. Consider also how you or someone in your life may be a "pushover".

context: To dream that you are pushed or being pushed
meaning: suggests that you are being coerced into doing something. You are facing a lot of pressure. Alternatively, the dream implies that you do not have enough time to complete a task. You strive for perfection.

context: To do push ups in your dream
meaning: indicates that you need to take more initiative and get these accomplished. It is time to utilize your potential and be more assertive. In particular, if you are doing one-handed push ups, then it means that you need to better exert yourself.

context: To see or use pushpins in your dream
meaning: indicate that you need to open your eyes and look at what is in front on you. You may be overlooking something that is in plain view.

context: To dream that you are handling putty
meaning: represents some situation, person, or relationship that you are still molding and forming. Also consider the phrase "like putty in your hands" to mean how you or someone is being easily influenced.

context: To see or do a jigsaw puzzle in your dream
meaning: represents a mental challenge or problem that you need to solve in your waking life. If there are pieces missing in the puzzle, then it suggest that you do not have all the facts needed to make an informed decision.

context: To see or do a crossword puzzle in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are being faced with a mental challenge. The dream may be a pun on "cross words" directed at you or aimed toward someone.

context: To see a pyramid in your dream
meaning: symbolizes longevity and stability. You have built a solid foundation for success. Alternatively, the dream suggests that major changes will occur over a short period of time.

context: To dream that you are climbing a pyramid
meaning: indicates that you will find gratification and fulfillment through perseverance.

context: To see pyrite in your dream
meaning: indicates that something is too good to be true. Remember that things are not always what it seems.

context: To see the letter "L" in your dream
meaning: is symbolic of loser. Alternatively, the dream may suggests that you need to take a break from whatever you are doing. The letter L may also signify your fear of the "l-word". You cannot even bring your dreaming mind to express love.

context: To see or wear a lab coat in your dream
meaning: symbolizes your protective nature. Alternatively, the dream implies your desire to sanitize a situation. Perhaps you are even trying to cover it up.

context: To dream that you are labeling something
meaning: represents your need for organization and order. Alternatively, it may also indicates that you are too quick to label something and pigeonhole it. Perhaps you are the one being labeled.

context: To see or read labels in your dream
meaning: indicate that you have unknowingly exposed certain private matters, due to your carelessness and neglect.

context: To dream that something is mislabeled
meaning: indicates that you are looking at things the wrong way. Try another perspective.

context: To dream that a label is missing on something
meaning: indicates that you are feeling lost. You are in need of some direction.

context: To dream that you are laboring
meaning: suggests that your goals will take a lot of hard work to accomplish.

context: If you are a woman and dream that you are in labor
meaning: indicates your desire to be pregnant and to start a family. To experience or feel pre-term labor pains or Braxton Hicks contractions in your dream indicate the anticipation of hard work ahead. If you are actually pregnant, then the dream serves as a rehearsal for the actual birth. The dream is trying to prepare you for labor and proper breathing.

context: To dream that someone goes into labor prematurely
meaning: implies that you need to be better prepared for unexpected challenges that may come your way.

context: To dream that you are in a laboratory
meaning: suggests that you are experimenting with your inner feelings, beliefs, or fears. You are testing yourself or some relationship. Alternatively, being in a laboratory means you are going through some sort of transformation.

context: To see a Labrador in your dream
meaning: is a sign that you are on the right path. The Labrador may also be sending you a message of loyalty, commitment and unconditional love. Perhaps these are things that you need to build or work on in your waking relationships.

context: To see or dream that you are in a labyrinth
meaning: indicates your desires to get to the center of some issue or problem. Alternatively, it suggests that you are feeling trapped in some situation. You feel lost and that there is no way out.

context: To see lace in your dream
meaning: points to your sensuality and femininity. Alternatively, it denotes tradition and old fashioned ideals. Perhaps you are being overly practical in some area of your life.

context: To watch or play lacrosse in your dream
meaning: symbolizes teamwork and cooperation. You can achieve your goals through hard work and dedication. Alternatively, the dream is a metaphor for the game of sex. Your behavior and game play represents your attitudes toward sex.

context: To dream that you are lactating
meaning: refers to your strong maternal bond and instincts. If you are leaking or squirting milk, then it implies your enthusiasm or desire to be a mother. Referred to as "letdown", the dream may also be a metaphor that someone is letting you down.

context: To dream that you are climbing up a ladder
meaning: suggests that you have reached a new level of achievement. It is symbolic of prosperity, hard work and your efforts. Consider also the phrase of "climbing the social ladder" in which you have achieved a promotion, a higher status, more power, or an important goal. Alternatively, it indicates meditation and prayer. You are setting forth on a spiritual path and higher awareness. Each rung of the ladder is symbolic of a stage in your spiritual awareness. The dream may also highlight how you are looking things from a different perspective.

context: To dream that you are climbing down a ladder
meaning: suggests that you are escaping from your spiritual responsibilities. It is an indication of future disappointments.

context: To dream that you are walking under a ladder
meaning: signifies bad luck. Perhaps you are having regrets over a decision you made.

context: To dream that someone is holding a ladder for you
meaning: indicates that you will find success if you have the support of others. You will rise to a level of prominence.

context: To dream that you fall from a ladder
meaning: denotes the hardships, risks or failures you are faced with in your endeavors.

context: To see a broken ladder in your dream
meaning: indicates consistent failures in your undertakings. You may feel that you are being handicapped in pursuing your goals.

context: To dream that you escape by
meaning: means of a ladder signifies that you will be successful after much struggle and obstacles.

context: To see a ladle in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are being nourished with love. It is symbolic of healing and comfort. Also consider what you are ladling.

context: To see a broken ladle
meaning: denotes grief and sorrow in love.

context: To see a ladybug in your dream
meaning: symbolizes beauty and good luck. The dream may also be a metaphor for a lady who is bugging you in your waking life. Perhaps there is an issue that you need to address with this lady. If the ladybug is unusually big, then it is analogous to the magnitude of the problem.

context: To see a lagoon in your dream
meaning: signifies some misunderstanding and doubt in what you are saying. Alternatively, it symbolizes stagnant emotions.

context: To see or dream that you are in an animal lair
meaning: symbolizes your subconscious mind. It signals self discovery. Alternatively, it represents a place where you feel safe and protected. Figure out what or who you are hiding from. Consider also the type of animal lair and look up the significance of that particular animal.

context: To see a lake in your dream
meaning: signifies your emotional state of mind. You feel restricted and that you can't express your emotions freely. Alternatively, the lake may provide you with solace, security, and peace of mind. If the lake is clear and calm, then it symbolizes your inner peace. If the lake is disturbed, then you may be going through some emotional turmoil.

context: To see a lamb in your dream
meaning: symbolizes deception. The lamb is also representative of something vulnerable, pure and innocent. Consider the metaphor "as gentle as a lamb".

context: To dream that you are holding a lamb in your arms
meaning: refers to the sacrifices in your life.

context: To see or drive a Lamborghini in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are moving too quickly and aggressively in some area of your life. You are living life in the fast lane.

context: To dream that you or someone is lame
meaning: signifies disappointments and failures in realizing your hopes and desires. Ask yourself who or what is holding you back. You may have lost your confidence. Don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it.

context: To lament for something in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are still in mourning over a loss. Alternatively, the dream suggests that you need to stop feeling sorry for yourself and have a more positive outlook in your life. Only after overcoming your issues and adversities will you enjoy pleasure and realize personal gains.

context: To see Lamia in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are rejecting your inner child. Alternatively, dreaming of Lamia indicates that a woman figure in your life who may be untrustworthy or cutthroat. She may be sucking away your energy and/or resources.

context: To see a lamp in your dream
meaning: symbolizes guidance, hope, inspiration, enlightenment and reassurance. If the lamp is dimly lit or unlit, then it suggests that you are feeling overwhelmed by emotional issues. You have lost your ability to find your own way or see things clearly.

context: To see a broken lamp in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are shutting out those who are trying to help you. It is also symbolic of disappointments, misfortune and bad luck.

context: To see a lamppost in your dream
meaning: indicates that light needs to be shed on some dark situation. Alternatively, the dream suggests that you are coming out of a depressing or gloomy phase.

context: To see a lampshade in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are seeking protection from some intense energy or power. You may be trying to shield yourself or be less noticeable.

context: To see or dream that you are in a lanai
meaning: indicates that you are open-mined and easy-going. You are receptive to new ideas. As a Hawaiian island, it symbolizes your need to escape and get away from your daily responsibilities. Give yourself a vacation.

context: To see a lance in your dream
meaning: represents initiative and direction. You have set your sight on a goal or path and are taking a firm stance on your beliefs. The lance is also symbolic of masculine power and may have phallic connotations.

context: To dream that you are wounded by a lance
meaning: denotes that you have made a poor judgment and are facing the consequences.

context: To see land in your dream
meaning: represents your need to be more grounded or down to earth. You are looking for a strong foundation and some stability. Alternatively, the dream may be a metaphor for something that you have "landed" as in a job, a part in a play, etc.

context: To see rocky or barren land
meaning: denotes failure in your undertakings.

context: To see or set a land mine in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are under some extreme pressure or stress. You fear making mistakes or tripping up on some project. Alternatively, a land mine symbolizes emotions or issues that can potentially explode if they are not properly addressed.

context: To dream that you are riding in a landau
meaning: represents light-hearted companionships.

context: To see an overturned landau in your dream
meaning: indicates that the good times are about to come to an abrupt end.

context: To see a landfill in your dream
meaning: represents ideas that you have discarded. It also refers to rejected aspects of yourself or of someone's character. You may be trying to confront or come to terms with these rejections.

context: To see the landing of an aircraft in your dream
meaning: signifies completion of a journey or some task. Some issues that were previously out of control have been resolved.

context: To see your landlord in your dream
meaning: represents the part of yourself that is always in control. It refers to your rational and responsible side. Perhaps you need to show more restraint and control in certain areas of your psyche.

context: To dream of various landscapes in your dream
meaning: represent where you are in your life or in your relationships. How do you see yourself with respect to the rest of the world and those around you? Consider what is going on in the landscape and how it may parallel your own waking life. In particular, a barren or dry landscape depicts dissatisfaction in your love life. According to Freud, the dream landscape symbolizes the human body. A landscape with gentle contours symbolize the female body, while a rocky landscape represents the male body. Also consider the feelings that the landscape invokes.

context: To dream of ever changing landscapes
meaning: indicates psychological transitions or emotional progress. It represents the various stages in your life. Alternatively, it may be offering you various viewpoints in looking at the same idea or situation. Something may be slipping away from your grasp. Look at the symbolism of key elements in the landscape.

context: To see a landslide in your dream
meaning: represents emotions that you have been holding back for a long time. You are on the verge of emotional overload. Your emotions are erupting in an unexpected or violent way. The dream may also symbolize the stresses in your life and all the responsibilities that rest on your shoulders.

context: To dream that you are changing lanes
meaning: indicate your impatience. It also means that you need to change your attitude and your way of thinking.

context: To dream that you are studying a language
meaning: suggests that you are having difficulties expressing your thoughts. You are confronted with an unfamiliar problem that you do not know how to approach and resolve.

context: To hear foul or vulgar language in your dream
meaning: signifies an embarrassing situation.

context: To hear or speak a foreign language in your dream
meaning: indicates a message from your subconscious that you do not yet understand.

context: To see or carry a lantern in your dream
meaning: represents the feelings and wisdom that are radiating from within you. These qualities will serve to guide you through life's journey.

context: To notice your lap in your dream
meaning: implies opportunities or problems. It also refers to loneliness and loss.

context: To dream that you are sitting on someone's lap
meaning: represents your search for stability and security.

context: To dream that you are holding someone on your lap
meaning: signifies your caring and supportive nature. Alternatively, the dream implies that you are open to criticism.

context: To give or perform a lap dance in your dream
meaning: suggests that you may be repressing your sexual desires. Perhaps you are feeling inhibited in discussing your sexual pleasures.

context: To see or receive a lap dance in your dream
meaning: indicates your need for a little more excitement in your sex life. Or you are looking for some intimacy.

context: To see a lapis in your dream
meaning: suggests that no one is perfect. You need to accept yourself along with your imperfections. Look within your own self and your inner strength. Alternatively, the dream represents success, wisdom and divine power.

context: To see or use a laptop in your dream
meaning: represents your need to reach out and communicate with others in any circumstance.

context: To dream that your laptop is missing or stolen
meaning: indicates that you are relying too much on your social network. You need to try and make it on your own abilities and merit.

context: To see or eat lard in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to be vigilant about cutting out the negativities in your life. Alternatively, the dream represents your concerns over food and health issues.

meaning: #Ref:big

context: To see larks flying in your dream
meaning: symbolize high aspirations. If they fall during flight, then it indicates your fall from grace and loss of innocence.

context: To hear larks singing in your dream
meaning: signify success, pleasure and joy. You need to consider a change of environment in order to find happiness.

context: To see a larva in your dream
meaning: symbolizes a rebirth. You are undergoing some inner changes and transformation.

context: To dream that you have laryngitis
meaning: indicates a loss of identity and a lack of personal power. You are unable to speak up and stand up for yourself. Alternatively, the dream points to your inability to convey a certain message. You are not sure how to put into words what you want to say to somebody.

context: To dream that you are in Las Vegas
meaning: refers to excess and overindulgence. You need to show some restraint in some area of your life. Alternatively, to dream of Vegas suggests that your good judgment is being clouded by all the emotional turmoil and chaos.

context: To see or eat lasagna in your dream
meaning: symbolizes warmth and comfort. Alternatively, it denotes the layers of your emotions.

context: To see a laser in your dream
meaning: symbolizes clarity and truth. You are seeing and understanding things much more clearly. Alternatively, it suggests that you need to focus your attention and concentrate on one task at a time.

context: To dream that you are swinging a lasso
meaning: suggests that there is some situation, object or relationship that you are trying to hold on to. Consider the significance of what you are lassoing.

context: To see a latch in your dream
meaning: symbolizes your sense of security. It refers to the things you reveal and the aspects of yourself that you keep to yourself.

context: To dream that you are late
meaning: signifies your fear of change and your ambivalence about seizing an opportunity. You may feel unready, unworthy, or unsupported in your current circumstances. Additionally, you may be overwhelmed or conflicted with decisions about your future. Time is running out and you no longer have time to accomplish all the things you want. Alternatively, being late in your dream could be telling you that it is better late than never.

context: To dream that you are studying Latin
meaning: indicates your position of prominence and distinction. It also refers to your scholarly pursuits.

context: To dream that you or someone is taking laudanum
meaning: represents your lack of willpower. You are easily persuaded and influenced by others.

context: To hear laughing or dream that you are laughing
meaning: suggests that you need to lighten up and let go of your problems. Don't put so much pressure on yourself. Laughing is also a sign of joyous release and pleasure. If you are being laughed at, then it indicates your insecurities and fears of not being accepted.

context: To hear evil, demonic laughing in your dream
meaning: represents feelings of humiliation and/or helplessness. You feel that someone is working against you.

context: To inhale laughing gas in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are being too serious or uptight. You need to lighten up. Alternatively, laughing gas implies that you are trying to numb yourself from some emotional pain. You are trying to escape from your waking problems.

context: To see a successful launch in your dream
meaning: indicates that a new project or relationship is taking off.

context: To see a failed launch in your dream
meaning: represents failed attempts and disappointments. There is a weakness in your way of thinking.

context: To dream that you are at a Laundromat
meaning: represents a transformation or cleansing. You are ready to rid yourself of past hurts. It is time for new changes.

context: To dream that you are doing your laundry
meaning: suggests that you are cleaning up your act or changing your image. Perhaps, you are too concerned about how you appear to others.

context: To dream that you are sorting the laundry
meaning: indicates that you are trying to understand your own feelings and sort your attitudes.

context: To see a laundry chute in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are not allowing others dictate how your should look or act. Your mind is your own. Alternatively, it signifies exploration of your subconscious and/or acknowledgement of your negative emotions.

context: To see or wear a laurel in your dream
meaning: symbolizes success and victory. You have overcome a difficult task and are being rewarded for a job well done. Alternatively, the dream may be a pun on someone who is named "Laurel" in your life.

context: To see lava in your dream
meaning: signifies violent anger which you have kept inside for a period of time.

context: To see a lava lamp in your dream
meaning: represents slow, fluid motion. Something in your waking life is moving in a similar fashion as the lava lamp. Perhaps, you are taking your time to do something and making sure it is thorough. Consider the color of the lava lamp for clues.

context: To see lavender in you dream
meaning: indicates mysticism and spiritual cleansing.
