meaning: #Ref:abyss

context: To see or wear a chastity belt in your dream
meaning: signifies your attitudes and feelings toward sex. Alternatively, the dream may be a metaphor to indicate that you are being overly protective. Perhaps your way of thinking is outdated.

context: To dream that you are in a chat room
meaning: represents your need to connect with others on a mental level. The dream could also mean that you are spending too much time in front of the computer and this has carried over into your dreams. You need to get out and socialize in the real world.

context: To dream that you are a chauffeur
meaning: indicates that you are helping someone with their goals. You are trying to steer them on the right direction.

context: To dream that you are being chauffeured
meaning: signifies extravagance and luxury. You have a high sense of self worth. Alternatively, the dream represents your dependence on others. You are not in control of your life.

context: To dream that you or someone is cheap
meaning: represents your own feelings of inadequacy. You are not fully acknowledging your own self worth.

context: To dream that you got something at a cheap price
meaning: suggests that you are being undervalued. Or are you cheating somebody of their valuable things? Consider the symbolism of the item and how you feel about it in the dream.

context: To dream that you are cheating on your spouse mate, fianc, or significant other
meaning: suggests feelings of self-guilt and self-betrayal. You may have compromised your beliefs or integrity and/or wasting your energy and time on fruitless endeavors. Alternatively, cheating dreams reflect the intensity of your sexual passion; you are exploring areas of your sexuality. In this scenario, the dream may actually serve as a reaffirmation of your commitment. Furthermore, if you are approaching your own wedding date, then it is not uncommon to have dreams about erotic experiences with partners other than your intended spouse. Most likely, such a dream represents the newness of your sexual passion. It may also signify anxieties of changing your identity - that of a spouse.

context: To dream that your mate, spouse, or significant other is cheating on you
meaning: indicates your fears of being abandoned. You may feel a lack of attention in the relationship. Alternatively, you may feel that you are not measuring up to the expectations of others. This notion may stem from issues of trust or self-esteem. The dream could also indicate that you are subconsciously picking up hints and cues that your significant other is not being completely truthful or is not fully committed in the relationship.

context: To dream that your friend is being cheated on
meaning: indicates your subconscious dislike for his/her significant other. You think your friend deserves to be treated better.

context: To dream that you are cheating at a game
meaning: suggests that you are not being honest with yourself. You feel inadequate and insecure.

context: To see a check in your dream
meaning: suggests that you may feel indebted to others. The dream may also be a pun on checking things out.

context: To see a blank check in your dream
meaning: symbolizes your unused potential. It may also indicate unclaimed rewards.

context: To see a check mark in your dream
meaning: indicates approval and acceptance. Your hard work has paid off.

context: To see a checkerboard in your dream
meaning: indicates the many aspects and facets of your personality. Alternatively, a checkerboard may reflect your struggle between good and evil or good and bad. The dream may also be a metaphor for your "checkered" past. Perhaps you did something that you were not proud of or something that is coming back to haunt you.

context: To see or play checkers in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to have a clear strategy in order to overtake your opponents. The dream may also be a pun on "check her". Perhaps you need to reevaluate this female person.

context: To dream that you are at a checkout
meaning: symbolizes completion. You feel whole. Alternatively, being at a checkout in your dream implies that you are not fully vested in a situation. You want to get out of some relationship or circumstance.

meaning: signifies life energy, enthusiasm and vitality. If the cheeks are sunken in, then it symbolizes sadness, hunger, poverty and/or struggles. The emphasis of cheeks in your dream could also point to health issues.

context: To dream that your cheeks are painted
meaning: represents your attitudes of courage and violence/passivity.

context: To dream that you are kissing someone on the cheek or someone is kissing you on the cheek,
meaning: then it signifies admiration, courtesy, reverence, friendship or respect.

context: To hear or start a cheer in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are headed in the right direction or making the right decisions in your life. You have more self confidence and belief in yourself. The dream may also be a metaphor to "cheer up".

context: To see or eat Cheerios in your dream
meaning: indicates that there is something missing from your life. You do not feel completely whole. Alternatively, the dream may be a pun on "farewell" or "good bye".

context: To see a cheerleader in your dream
meaning: represents competition and triumph. Your dream may be telling you to offer more praise and encouragement toward others.

context: To dream that you are a cheerleader
meaning: signifies your self-confidence and self-esteem. You need to be more active and more positive in some waking situation in your life.

context: To see cheese in your dream
meaning: symbolizes gains and profits. Alternatively, the dream may be a metaphor for something that is "cheesy" or lame. Or it could be saying that you need to smile more.

meaning: indicates that you are leaving some evidence or clue of your indulgent or negative behavior. Alternatively, the dream may just mean that you have a strong craving for cheese curls.

meaning: indicates that things are going great for you. You deserve a sweet reward for a job well done.

context: To see a cheetah in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to get moving and be more active in pursuit of your goals. Perhaps you have been a little lazy and you need to get off from that seat.

context: To dream that you are a chef
meaning: indicates that you have the ability, knowledge, and talent to chose your path in life. You know what course of action you need to take and are moving forward in a productive manner. And you have learned from your previous life experiences.

context: To see a chef in your dream
meaning: represents transformation and changes. Consider what is "cooking" in your life?

context: To see or use chemicals in your dream
meaning: suggest that you are undergoing some transformation and individuation process.

context: To dream that you are mixing or combining chemicals
meaning: represent creativity, manipulation and/or intellectual power.

meaning: points to your ability to change your Self. You alter your persona according to the situation.

meaning: refers to manipulation. You are being manipulated or you are the one that is doing the manipulating.

context: To see cherries in your dream
meaning: symbolize honesty and truthfulness or sweetness and good fortune. Alternatively, the dream may be telling you that "life is like a bowl of cherries". In other words, don't take life so seriously; take it easy.

context: To see a cherry tree in your dream
meaning: represents luck, spring, femininity, and youth.

context: To see a cherry blossom tree in your dream
meaning: symbolizes feminine power, beauty and love. The dream may be telling you that you can be both strong and delicate at the same time. Alternatively, dreaming of a cherry blossom tree symbolizes mortality. It may also be a reminder that life is short and to take advantage of what life has to offer.

context: To see a cherub in your dream
meaning: represents child-like innocence, frailty and mischievousness. You need to take life a little less seriously. Alternatively, the dream indicates that you may have been dishonest or manipulative.

context: To see the Cheshire cat in your dream
meaning: signifies mischief, deceit and mockery. It may represent someone in your life who you are not sure if you can trust or rely on.

context: To see or play chess in your dream
meaning: indicates that you need to carefully think through the situation before making a decision. The light and dark squares of the chess board symbolizes the positive (pro) and negative (con) of a situation. The dream may also comment on how you have met your match in love or in business.

context: To dream that your king chess piece is in danger
meaning: suggests that you are being stifled by some female character in your life.

context: To dream of chess pieces coming alive
meaning: means that you are completely engrossed or submerged in some situation, relationship or task. You are ignoring everything else around you. Alternatively, the dream implies that you no longer have control of a situation. A situation in your waking life is ruling your actions and behavior.

context: To see your chest in your dream
meaning: signifies confidence, conquest and vitality. Alternatively, it represents feelings of being overwhelmed and being dangerously confronted by something. Consider also if the dream is telling you that there is something that you need to "get off your chest".

meaning: indicates triumph and a great accomplishment.

context: Chest
meaning: It is common for those who experience real life chest pains to have dreams where they are being shot in the chest or feel heavy pressure on their chest.

context: Dreaming of a storage chest or a wooden chest
meaning: is symbolic of suppressing your own needs or feelings. You tend to put other's needs ahead of your own. Alternatively, a storage chest represents memories that you are holding onto.

context: To see a chestnut tree in your dream
meaning: represents strength and good health.

context: To see a chevron in your dream
meaning: symbolizes protection.

context: To dream that you are chewing something
meaning: suggests that you are sorting things out and carefully thinking it over.

context: To dream that you are in Chicago
meaning: represents mainstream thinking. Known as the windy city, the dream may also indicate that your life is blowing in a new direction. You are experiencing extra vigor, vitality and energy in your life.

meaning: symbolizes youthful curiosity and innocence. The dream may also be a slang for a girl.

context: To see a chickadee in your dream
meaning: indicates that you need to pay attention and become aware of something unique and special occurring in your life.

meaning: implies that your subconscious is calling you a chicken. You are lacking confidence in yourself.

meaning: symbolize cowardliness and a lack of willpower. The dream may be a pun on being a chicken or chickening out of some situation. Chickens also represent excessive chatter and gossip. Listen closely to what people may be saying about you or what you are saying about others.

context: To see a rubber chicken in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are being too serious and need to lighten up. It is okay to be silly sometimes.

context: To dream that you are eating chicken
meaning: implies fear. You are being a "chicken". In particular, if you are eating fried chicken, then it refers to some unhealthy aspect that you need to cut from your life. Perhaps you are being too overindulgent. If you are eating raw chicken in your dream, then it indicates that you are feeling unprepared about some situation. You are having difficulties achieving your goals.

context: To see a police chief in your dream
meaning: indicates that you need to take accountability for your actions. There is a higher authority that you need to answer to. Alternatively, a police chief symbolizes a father figure in your waking life. Your attitude or impression of the chief is a reflection of your waking relationship with this father figure.

context: To see or wear chiffon in your dream
meaning: represents your feminine and delicate side. It may also point to your vulnerabilities.

context: To see a Chihuahua in your dream
meaning: represents someone around you who is unexpectedly vocal. It may also represent someone who is insecure. Alternatively, the dream may refer to a situation or relationship where the bark is larger than the bite.

context: To dream that you are a small child again
meaning: suggests that you are feeling the burdens of adulthood. You are trying to escape from your daily responsibility and are looking for someone else to shield, protect and care for you.

context: To dream that you lose a child
meaning: represents losing hope. It may also suggest that a project is not working out as you had wanted it to.

context: To save a child in your dream
meaning: signifies your attempts to save a part of yourself from being destroyed. If you dream that you are separated from your children, then it symbolizes failure in some personal endeavor or a setback in some ideal you had.

context: To see a child fall down in your dream
meaning: denotes lost innocence.

context: To dream of your childhood
meaning: indicates your wish to return to a life where you had little responsibility and worries. It also represents innocence. Alternatively, it suggests that certain aspects of your childhood has not yet been integrated into your adult personality. On the other hand, some childhood anxiety has yet to be resolved in your adult life.

context: To see children in your dream
meaning: signify an aspect of yourself and your childlike qualities. You may be retreating back to a childlike state and longing for the past. You are trying to still satisfy repressed desires and unfulfilled hopes. Perhaps there is something that you need to see grow and nurture. Take some time off and cater to the inner child within. Alternatively, the dream may be highlighting your innocence, purity, simplicity, and carefree attitude. If you are fighting with children, then it implies that you are repressing your inner child. The children could represent someone in your waking life (coworker, mate, sibling, etc.) who is acting like a child. If you see children fighting in your dream, then it means that your sense of morality and character are in conflict.

context: To forget about your child or children
meaning: suggests that you are feeling overwhelmed by your waking responsibilities. The dream is telling you that you are overly fixating on minor details and overlooking the important things on your life. You need to re-prioritize your time and focus on what matters. To dream that your own grown children are still very young indicates that you still see them as young and dependent. You want to feel needed and significant. To dream that you have more children that you actually have in real life means that you are discovering old talents or skills that you have been casting aside.

context: Children
meaning: To dream that you are watching children but they do not know you are there is a metaphor for some hidden knowledge or some latent talent which you have failed to recognize.

context: To save a child in your dream
meaning: signifies your attempts to save a part of yourself from being destroyed. If you dream that you are separated from your children, then it symbolizes failure in some personal endeavor or a setback in some ideal you had.

context: To see children being abused in your dream
meaning: implies that you are lacking a voice for your own inner child. You feel that a part of your own childhood is lost.

context: To see or eat chili in your dream
meaning: symbolizes intense passion and raw emotion. The dream may also be a metaphor for being "chilly".

context: To get the chills in your dream
meaning: signify fear. Alternatively, it represents your indifference to some situation or person. The dream may be an actual physical reaction; perhaps the blankets have fallen off of you. Or the dream may be a metaphor indicating that you need to "chill out" or calm down.

context: To see a chimera in your dream
meaning: represents a feeling of confusion. You need to sort out your thoughts and emotions.

context: To hear chimes in your dream
meaning: symbolize tranquility. Alternatively, it means that there is something that you need to pay special attention to.

meaning: indicates your need to vent off your frustrations and get things out in the open. You need to release all that negativity and/or guilt that you are holding in.

context: To see a chimpanzee in your dream
meaning: suggests that what you thought was true is actually not. You are over-thinking an issue.

context: To notice your chin in your dream
meaning: refers to your resilience and your ability to bounce back from adversity. The chin often symbolizes character, strength, and resolve. Perhaps you need to "keep your chin up" and remain optimistic.

Alternatively, dreaming of a chinchilla suggests that you are high maintenance and in need of a lot of attention. Because chinchillas are desired because of their ultra soft fur, the dream may also reflect your stance on the fur industry.

context: To see a chipmunk in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are holding on to the past and need to learn to let go.

context: To see a chiropractor in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are seeking support and advice. Don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it; it is not a sign of weakness.

context: To see or use a chisel in your dream
meaning: indicates that you need to forcibly break through the surface or barrier in order to get to the core of the situation or problem.

context: To see or eat chives in your dream
meaning: suggest that you get along well with others. The dream symbolizes harmony and balance.

context: To dream that you have chlamydia
meaning: points to your negative attitude about sex. The dream may also be a warning that you need to practice safer sex.

meaning: signifies love, celebration and self-reward. It also suggests that you may be indulging in too many excesses and need to practice some restraint.

context: To eat chocolate in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are embracing your own sensuality.

context: If you dream that chocolate is melting,
meaning: then it implies disappointments that you are experiencing in your waking life. Alternatively, dreaming of melted chocolate means that you need to adapt to some change.

meaning: means that you are feeling good about life.

meaning: symbolizes spiritual harmony and balance. It also refers to your ability to work and cooperate with others. If you are singing out of tune, then it suggests that you are not fitting into some group situation.

context: To see or wear a choker in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are having difficulties in expressing yourself. You maybe feeling constricted or voiceless in some waking situation.

context: Choking dreams are often a fearful experience and it is not uncommon for dreamers to awaken from them. To dream that you are choking on an object
meaning: suggests that you may find some advice/remarks/situation hard to swallow or difficult to accept. Alternatively, you may feel that you are unable to completely express yourself in a situation. In particular, if you are choking on food, then it may be an expression of self-guilt and unnurtured feelings. If you are choking on smoke, then it indicates something you are unwilling to confront.

context: To dream that someone is choking you
meaning: indicates that you are suppressing your emotions. You have difficulties in expressing your fears, anger, or love. Consider the phrase "being all choked up". Alternatively, you may feel that you are being prevented or restricted from freely expressing yourself.

context: To dream that you are choking someone
meaning: signifies feelings of aggression. You may be trying to prevent something from being said or revealed.

context: To dream that you are chopping something
meaning: indicates that you are trying to cut your problems into smaller, more manageable sizes. You need to break up the issues and attack them piece by piece. Consider also the significance of the object that you are chopping. Alternatively, the dream may be a metaphor for having the chops or the guts and fortitude to do something.

context: To see or use a chopping board or chopping block in your dream
meaning: means that you need to take a risk or a stand. Be more decisive. Consider the idiom of "being on the chopping block." Perhaps you are at risk of losing your job or being let go fo some commitment. Your performance is being scrutinized and questioned.

context: To see or use chopsticks in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are trying to manipulate some situation. Alternatively, it represents an extension of your reach.

context: If you are using chopsticks for its unintended function,
meaning: then it suggest that you are in a sticky situation.

context: To dream that you are a choreographer
meaning: represents freedom of expression. You feel unconstrained, unrestricted, and in charge of the direction that your life is taking. Your life is balanced and in harmony.

meaning: #Ref:housework

meaning: highlights an unwavering loyalty. You are also a little overly protective.

meaning: represents perfection of the self and spiritual truth. You need to achieve self-fulfillment through love. This symbol has many personal associations for you, depending on your belief.

context: To dream of a christening

meaning: signifies a transitional phase of self exploration. It signals spiritual enlightenment, emotional growth, physical prowess, new opportunities and mental passages in your life.

context: If you are walking through a long corridor,
meaning: then it represents your desperation in trying to escape a repetitive situation or some behavior patterns. You need to free yourself of this repetition. Alternatively, it symbolizes the choices and options that are available to you. You have a lot of things to consider.

context: To see or wear a corsage in your dream
meaning: suggests that an aspect of yourself is looking to be acknowledged and recognized. Alternatively, it is a symbol of honor.

context: To see or wear a corset in your dream
meaning: indicates submission, restraint and restrictions. You may be feeling limited. Alternatively, it may mean that you have a tendency to hold in your displeasure in order to please others.

context: #Ref:makeup
meaning: #Ref:makeup

context: To see or notice the cost of something in your dream
meaning: represents the value you are placing on yourself, your time and your abilities. If the cost is high, then it indicates that you value yourself highly. If the cost is low, then you are undervaluing yourself or taking somebody else for granted. The dream also relates to your self esteem.

context: To dream that you are wearing a costume
meaning: indicates that you are putting on a facade toward others. You do not want to reveal your true self and are not being completely honest with people around you.

context: To dream that you are at a costume party
meaning: suggests that you are trying to escape from the demands of real life. You want to enjoy life and not worry about your daily responsibilities.

context: To see a cottage in your dream
meaning: represents comfort peace and serenity. You prefer a quiet life of simplicity. The cottage may also represent an altered sense of reality and thus may be a means of escaping the responsibilities and problems that may be associated with your home. You need to approach life's difficulties one at a time.

context: To dream that you are picking cotton
meaning: suggests that you are seeing little benefits from all your long hard work. It may also mean that aspects of yourself are in harmony.

context: To dream that you are wearing cotton
meaning: symbolizes simplicity.

context: To see or use a cotton ball in your dream
meaning: indicates that you need to apply yourself and focus on some important project. Alternatively, a cotton ball symbolizes pureness or softness. Perhaps there is a relationship or situation that requires a more delicate touch.

context: To see or eat cotton candy in your dream
meaning: represents childhood pleasures or rewards. You are content with the way things are going in your life.

context: To see or dream that you are on a couch
meaning: represents rest, relaxation, laziness or boredom. It may also mean you need to clear you mind and thoughts. Consider also who is on the couch with you as the dream may also have sexual connotations.

context: To see a cougar in your dream
meaning: symbolizes wild beauty, power, grace, and raw emotion. It often refers to feminine power and aggression. Thus, the dream may represent a woman. Alternatively, it indicates lurking danger and death.

context: To see or take cough drops in your dream
meaning: indicate that you need some coaxing in order to discuss some issue. There is something holding you back.

context: To dream that you are coughing
meaning: represents your fear or dissatisfaction of the future. You need to put some distance between yourself and others. Alternatively, it indicates that you have made a negative choice in some important matter.

context: In particular, to dream that you are coughing blood
meaning: represents wasted energy. You are spending too much time on counterproductive activities.

context: To see or dream that you are a counselor or dream that you are one
meaning: suggests that you are seeking for some support and direction in your life. Pay important attention to what the counselor is saying and/or doing. Your dream is trying to convey a message that you need to think about and possibly act upon.

context: To stand in front of a counter in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are looking for advice and for some direction in your life. You are exploring your options. Depending on the function or purpose of the counter, the dream may also imply that you are lacking something in your life and are looking for a form of fulfillment. Alternatively, the counter may be a pun that you need to make a "counter" on some offer. Learn to compromise.

context: To see counterfeit money in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are feeling unworthy or that someone is devaluing your talents or efforts. Perhaps something is not what it appears to be. Alternatively, this dream symbol suggests that you are pretending to be something you are not.

context: To dream that you are counting
meaning: suggests that you are too rigid, obsessive-compulsive and overly disciplined. You need to relax a little. Alternatively the dream may be a metaphor for being the one that others can "count on". You are reliable and dependable.

context: To dream that you escape to another country
meaning: symbolizes change in your life. You are going through a new phase or transition. Consider how you feel about the surrounding. If you are afraid or lost, then it indicates that you are not ready for the change. You are not willing to leave the past behind. If you are excited or happy in this unknown place, then it suggests that you are ready for change.

context: Dreaming about your home country
meaning: indicates some unfinished feelings that you have left behind. A current situation may be forcing you to confront issues of your past. Alternatively, to dream of your home country represents loyalty and commitment to family.

context: To dream that you are in a country club
meaning: represents your status in society and sense of belong. You feel that you are part of a special group.

context: To dream of the countryside
meaning: suggests that you are seeking a simpler way of life. You need to take some time for yourself to relax and free your mind. Alternatively, it indicates a sense of freedom and/or openness that is lacking in your daily life.

context: To see a couple in your dream
meaning: symbolize marriage, your parents, or a relationship. Consider what the couple are doing in your dream for additional clues about their significance. It may point to something that is lacking or missing from your life.

context: To dream that you have great courage
meaning: indicates that you are willing to confront rejected aspects of your subconscious head on. You are about to come to a whole new understanding. The dream may be training you for what you need to do in your waking life.

context: To see or clip coupons in your dream
meaning: suggest that you are doing your best to maximize your resources. You need to be more frugal or conserve your energy.

context: To dream that you are in court standing up for charges against you
meaning: signifies your struggle with issues of fear and guilt. A situation or circumstance in your life is giving you much distress and worry. You feel that you are being judged in some way and need to defend yourself.

context: To see a courthouse in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are being judged.

context: To see your cousin in your dream
meaning: represents something or some aspect of your character that is somewhat familiar. Perhaps you need to spend more time in cultivating and developing some emerging ability or character. In particular, if you dream that your cousin is ignoring you, then it indicates that you are not acknowledging some aspect of yourself that is represented by your cousin.

context: To dream that you or your sibling is in love with a cousin
meaning: represents your acceptance of each other. You are acknowledging and embracing key qualities in one another.

context: To dream that you are covering something
meaning: indicates a part of yourself that you are trying to hide or are afraid of revealing. Consider what you are trying to cover up.

context: To see a cow in your dream
meaning: symbolizes your passive and docile nature. You obey others without question. Alternatively, a cow represents maternal instincts or the desire to be cared for. For some cultures, the cow represents divine qualities of fertility, nourishment and motherhood.

context: To see the skeleton of a cow
meaning: suggests that your mother or motherly figure in your waking life is displaying a lack of emotions. She is being unresponsive to your needs.

context: To see a herd of cows
meaning: indicates your need to belong.

context: To dream that you are milking a cow
meaning: represents your willingness and drive to work hard. In the end, you will benefit from your hard work.

context: To dream that you or someone is a coward
meaning: indicates that you are afraid to see your true Self and to be who you are. You are hindering your own self-growth.

context: To see or dream that you are a cowboy
meaning: symbolizes masculinity, ruggedness, and toughness. You are in control of your animalistic and instinctual side.

context: To see your coworkers in your dream
meaning: highlights aspects of your waking relationship with them, including difficulties/support. It signifies your ambition, struggles and competitive nature. If the coworkers in your dream are not your actual coworkers, then they may pertain to some psychological business that you need to work on. Work-related dreams can also often be linked to stress at work.

context: To dream that you are training someone to take your place
meaning: suggests that you are moving toward deeper inner development. You are leaving behind old attitudes and are looking toward the future.

context: To see or wear cowrie shells in your dream
meaning: signify your laid back and easy going attitude. Alternatively, a cowrie shell symbolizes fertility, womanhood, and reproduction. The dream may also be a metaphor for the value that you assign to certain things.

context: To see a coyote in your dream
meaning: denotes deception and weakness.

context: To dream that you are attacked by coyotes
meaning: indicates that you are struggling with your own selfish needs.

context: To dream that you are performing CPR on someone
meaning: indicates that you have resolved some anxiety, fear or tension in your life. Alternatively, the dream signifies creativity and intelligence.

context: To dream that someone is giving you CPR
meaning: suggests that you are feeling exhausted or emotionally drained. You are seeking advice.

context: To see a crab in your dream
meaning: signifies your perseverance and tenacity. On an extreme note, you maybe be too clingy and dependent. You are hanging on to a hopeless endeavor or relationship. Alternatively, the dream may indicate that you are trying to avoid some issue. You are being evasive. Crabs are also symbolic of your irritable personality, as in the pun, being "crabby".

context: To dream of a crack in some object
meaning: indicates that something in your life is imperfect. Nobody is perfect. Or there could be a flaw in your thinking or relationship. The dream may also be a pun on "cracking under pressure". You may be experiencing difficulties in trying to maintain your composure and keeping it together.

context: To see or eat a cracker in your dream
meaning: suggests that you tend to care for the needs of others before your own. You spend your time looking after other people and as a result, neglect your needs. The dream may also be a pun on "crack her". Perhaps you are trying to get someone to reveal certain information or secrets.

context: To see a cradle in your dream
meaning: symbolizes a dependent relationship. You may feel the need to be protected and cared for. Your dream may be telling you to regain some control and independence in your life. Alternatively, it represents a new project or fresh start.

context: To dream that you are making crafts
meaning: refers to your resourcefulness and your hands on approach to various situations. Alternatively, crafting in your dream may be a metaphor that you are being deceitful, cunning or manipulative.

context: To dream that you have a cramp
meaning: means that you need to stop what you are doing and reevaluate your choices or decisions. Alternatively, a cramp implies that you are overworked. Consider also the significance of where the cramp is located.

context: To see or eat cranberries in your dream
meaning: means longevity and good health. Alternatively, cranberries signify warmth and togetherness.

context: To drink cranberry juice in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to cut down on your stress.

context: To see a crane in your dream
meaning: represents happiness, maternal love, and your gestures of good will. You look out for those who are near and dear to you. Alternatively, a crane signifies tact, immortality or vigilance.

context: To dream that you are making a crank call
meaning: signifies your frustrations about not being taken seriously.

context: To dream that someone is crank calling you
meaning: indicates that you are feeling out of the loop. You feel that some information is being hidden from you.

context: To dream that you are in a car crash
meaning: indicates that your beliefs, lifestyle, or goals are clashing with another's. It may also represent a shocking situation or painful experience. Alternatively, car crashes may forewarn of your dangerous or careless driving habits. In particular, if a car crashes into you, then it suggests that your lifestyle, beliefs or goals may be in conflict with another's. It may also be symbolic of a jolting experience or injured pride.

context: To dream that a plane crashes
meaning: signifies that you have set overly high and unrealistic goals for yourself. You are in danger of having those goals come crashing down. Alternatively, the crashing airplane represents your lack of confidence, self-defeating attitude and self-doubt. You do not believe in your own ability to achieve those goals. Loss of power and uncertainty in achieving your goals are also signified.

context: Crash
meaning: To wake up before you crash in your dream may simply be the anticipation of the crash that jolts you awake. It is similar to the notion of waking up before you hit the ground from a fall.

context: To see a crash test dummy in your dream
meaning: refers to the impacts others are making on your life.

context: To see a crate in your dream
meaning: signifies your positive attitude, your potential, the possibilities and your drive for success.

context: To see a crater in your dream
meaning: indicates that aspects of your subconscious are being slowly revealed to you. This dream symbol is also symbolic of past memories and experiences.

context: To see a crawfish in your dream
meaning: represents your tenacity.

context: To see a crawl space in your dream
meaning: symbolizes your subconscious. If you are going through a crawl space, then it suggests that you are exploring aspects of your subconscious in a slow and careful manner.

context: To dream that you are crawling
meaning: indicates that you are approaching your goals with careful forethought and preparation. Alternatively, the dream may indicate that you are lowering yourself and your standards. You may be doing less than your best.

context: To dream that you are crawling out of a wreck or ruins
meaning: represents your willpower.

context: To dream that someone is crawling towards you
meaning: signifies your need for power, revenge, superiority, or control.

context: To see crayons in your dream
meaning: represent some childhood memory or a period of time where you were more carefree. It is also symbolic of creativity. You may need to think outside the lines into more unconventional thoughts and ways of doing things. Consider the symbolism of the color of the crayon.

context: To dream that you are going crazy
meaning: suggests that you have lost sight of your goals. You may feel that you are no longer able to depend on someone. Alternatively, you feel that your opinions, viewpoints or decisions are being unaccepted or being ignored. You may feel like an outsider.

context: To see or eat cream in your dream
meaning: indicates that you appreciate the minor and sweet things in life. It is symbolic of nurturance and richness.

context: To see or apply face cream in your dream
meaning: represents a beautiful soul. It may also represent the character and personality you are portraying to others in your waking life.

context: To see a faceless creature in your dream
meaning: indicates a situation you are refusing to see or confront, but are aware of it in some passive way. This dream also suggests that something in your life is bringing up feelings of fear and insecurities.

context: To dream that you are getting credit for something
meaning: represents acceptance of your responsibilities and duty. It also signifies your own sense of pride and confidence.

context: To dream about credit cards
meaning: relate to your worth, value and/or credibility. Depending on your waking experiences, the credit cards may symbolize being in debt and your attitudes about money, work, and thrift.

context: To dream that you owe money on your credit card
meaning: signifies an imbalance or some struggle in a personal situation or business matter. Alternatively, it may indicate that you are putting too much demands of others.

context: To dream that you lose your credit cards
meaning: indicate your carelessness in some aspect of your waking life.

context: To dream that someone is stealing your credit cards
meaning: suggest that something or someone is robbing you of vital energy.

context: To see a creek in your dream
meaning: represents personal energy flow and steady emotional release. Alternatively, the dream may indicate that you are in trouble or danger. Consider the saying to be "up a creek without a paddle."

context: To see a dried up creek
meaning: indicates that you are being cut off from your spiritual being and being out of touch with yourself. You may also feel physically or emotionally drained.

context: To see or use a creeper in your dream
meaning: indicates that you need to approach your goals from a different angle. You need a fresh new perspective on where your life is headed.

context: To see cremains in your dream
meaning: symbolizes change. It also represents a return to your true Self and acceptance of who you are.

context: To dream that someone is being cremated
meaning: represents purification and your strive for perfection. It symbolizes the ending to a phase in your life and the beginning of something else. If the person being cremated has passed away in real life, then the dream may be a way of grieving or coping with the loss. You want to always remember them in a positive light.

context: To see or eat a crepe in our dream
meaning: implies that you are doing your best to keep it together while still looking your best.

context: To see or wear a crepe fabric in your dream
meaning: suggests that life is not always as smooth as you want it to be. Enjoy life and learn from the little obstacles that it has to offer.

context: To see a crescent in your dream
meaning: represents the emergence of your feminine character. It also indicates versatility and changes.

context: To see a crib in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are harvesting or "babying" a new idea, creation or project. Alternatively, it may refer to your nurturing, protective, and caring nature. A more literal interpretation of this symbol suggests that you may be yearning for a baby or that you are expecting a baby. The dream may also be a pun on "your home".

context: To see crickets in your dream
meaning: represents introspection. You are seeking guidance.

context: To hear crickets in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are letting minor things bother you.

context: To dream that you or someone commits a crime
meaning: represents feelings of guilt and shame. Your inner fears are hindering your growth and progress.

context: To see crime scene tape in your dream
meaning: represents protection from your subconscious. Something is preventing you from delving deeper. Alternatively, the dream symbolizes restriction.

context: To dream that you are a criminal
meaning: indicates that you are looking for a short cut in life. You are selling yourself short and underestimating your own potential. Alternatively, the dream means that you feel you are entitled to certain things.

context: #Ref:handicap
meaning: #Ref:handicap

context: To dream that you are a critic
meaning: suggests that you are being overly judgmental of others or of some situation. Alternatively, the dream represents self-discipline.

context: To see crochet in your dream
meaning: indicates that you will find yourself entangled in some situation

context: To dream that you are crocheting
meaning: symbolizes your creativity and artistic abilities.

context: To see or use a crock pot in your dream
meaning: suggests that you need to look at various sources to attack a problem. Alternatively, it means that patience, hard work, and tenacity will pay off in the long run. Hang in there and don't let difficulties and obstacles discourage you.

context: To see a crocodile in your dream
meaning: symbolizes freedom, hidden strength and power. It also forewarns of hidden danger. Someone near you is giving you bad advice and is trying to sway you into poor decisions. Because crocodiles can live in water and on land, they also represent your conscious and subconscious and the emotional and rational. Perhaps something is coming to the surface and you are on the verge of some new awareness.

Alternatively, the crocodile may be an aspect of yourself and your aggressive and "snappy" attitude. Or it may reveal that you are being insincere, displaying false emotions and shedding "crocodile tears".

context: Dreaming that you are chased or bitten by a crocodile
meaning: implies that you are refusing to confront some painful, disturbing or destructive aspect of your subconscious. Your feelings toward a situation or relationship is suffocating you or is eating you up inside.

context: To see a crocus in your dream
meaning: represents lucidity and your need to think more clearly about a situation.

context: To dream that you are eating a croissant
meaning: indicates that you are lacking some affection or love in your life. There is a void waiting to be filled.

context: To see something crooked in your dream
meaning: indicates that something is not right or normal about a situation. The dream may also be a pun on someone who is a crook. You may be duped or lied to.

context: To dream that you are tending to your crop
meaning: represents growth, self-love, and self-appreciation. In the end, your hard work will pay off.

context: To see a cross in your dream
meaning: signifies suffering, martyrdom, death, and/or sacrifice. It is a symbol of your religious faith. Perhaps your dream is telling you that you have a cross to bear or that you are acting "crossed" and annoyed. Ask yourself what is causing you to suffer or what is causing you great difficulties.

context: Dreaming that a cross is swinging back and forth in a pendulum motion
meaning: suggests that you are wavering in your faith and/or questioning your belief system.

context: To dream that you or someone is cross-dressing
meaning: indicates that you need to express and acknowledge your masculine side if you are female or your feminine side if you are male.

context: To dream that you are crossing a street
meaning: suggests that you are putting yourself in harm's way. Alternatively, the dream indicates that you like to go against the majority. As a result, you become the target of criticism.

context: To dream that you are crossing a river or some body of water
meaning: symbolizes a spiritual change or reawakening.

context: To see crossbones in your dream
meaning: symbolizes danger and poison. The symbol may also represent the life of a pirate.

context: To see or use a crossbow in your dream
meaning: implies that you need to have more precision in the goals that you are reaching for. Try to accomplish your goals in a more direct manner.

context: To see a crossing gate in your dream
meaning: symbolizes temporary setbacks toward achieving your goals, especially if the gate is going down. If the gate is up, then it means that you have overcome certain obstacles in your life. You are not letting something or something get in your way of your goals.

context: To dream that you are at a crossroads
meaning: symbolize an important decision that you need to make. You have come to a point in your life where you have several options that you need to weigh. Each option will lead you to a different destination or goal. Alternatively, the crossroads suggest of a change in direction in your life.

context: To see or dream that you are in a crosswalk
meaning: means that you are careful about the risks you take.

context: To see or do a crossword puzzle
meaning: suggests that you are being faced with a mental challenge. The dream may be a pun on "cross words" directed at your or aimed toward someone.

context: To see or eat a crouton in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are feeling uninspired. You are in need of encouragement and motivation.

context: To see a crow in your dream
meaning: represents death and the darker aspects of your character. The dream could also be pointing out your annoying habits. Alternatively, the crow may be conveying a message from your subconscious.

context: To dream that crows are on the attack
meaning: indicates a conflict with your subconscious.

context: To dream that you kill a crow
meaning: implies that you are unable to or refuse to give up a habit.

context: To dream that a crow kills a person
meaning: represents an inescapable death. This death may be symbolic to an end to some situation, habit, or relationship in your waking life.

context: To see or use a crowbar in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are trying to get into your subconscious even though you may not be mentally ready to confront those issues. You are forcing things out.

context: To dream that you are attached with a crowbar
meaning: means that someone is making you confront some issue that you are not ready to deal with.

context: To dream that you are in or part of a crowd
meaning: suggests that you need some space for yourself. You need solitude to reflect on a situation and recharge your energy. Consider also the familiar phrase of "going along with the crowd" which implies conformity and lack of individuality. Perhaps you feel that your own opinion doesn't count or matter. Alternatively, dreaming of a crowd means that you need to incorporate the various aspects of the crowd into your own persona. If you dream that you are stopping a crowd from doing something, then it means that you have a tendency to go against what everyone else is doing or thinking.

context: To dream that you are not part of a crowd or that you separated yourself from a crowd
meaning: suggests that you are feeling left out. Alternatively, the dream symbolizes your individualism. You are your own person and you are not afraid to voice your own opinions.

context: To see an unruly crowd in your dream
meaning: signifies that the worries and problems around you are pressing in on you. You are expressing great distress.

context: To see a happy, orderly crowd in your dream
meaning: indicates that you have a strong social support system.

context: To see a crown in your dream
meaning: symbolizes success and prominence.

context: To dream that you are wearing a crown
meaning: suggests that you are in a position of power. Alternatively, you may be basking in your own achievements. You are recognizing your talents and accomplishments.

context: To see a crucifix in your dream
meaning: is symbolic of new life, spiritual guidance, and liberation. The dream may serve as a connection with your inner Christ/love consciousness. Alternatively, it represents your difficulties and hardships. Do you feel you are being crucified for something occurring in your life?

context: To see an upside down crucifix
meaning: implies that some aspect of your life is in disarray. You are not sure what to believe or what is right anymore. Things are not always what it seems. Alternatively, an upside down crucifix is symbolic of the pope.

context: To dream that you are being crucified
meaning: indicates that you are punishing yourself. You may be feeling guilty.

context: To dream that you or someone is being cruel
meaning: signifies the release of pent-up hostility and anger. You may need to acknowledge the shadow and negative aspects of your personality.

context: To dream that someone is being cruel to you
meaning: suggests that you need to develop your inner and outer strengths and become more emotionally strong.

context: To dream that you are on a cruise
meaning: represents some emotional journey that you are going through. The dream may also be a pun on "cruising" through situations in your life with ease and little effort.

context: To see or make crumbs in your dream
meaning: suggest that you are feeling left out. Do you feel like an outsider in some situation?

context: To dream that you are crushing something
meaning: denotes that you are under tremendous stress over a decision that you need to make. If you dream that a part of your body is being crushed, then it suggests that you are being prevented to full express yourself.

context: To dream that you have a crush on somebody is a literal reflection of your attraction and fascination for that person. To see your crush in your dream
meaning: represents your current infatuation with her or him. If you find yourself thinking about him during the day, then it is not surprising that his image will appear in your dream during the night. If you dream of your crush frequently or that your crush likes you back, then your dream maybe be telling you that it is time to let this person know how you feel, especially if you are dreaming of her or him in a good way. Only good things can happen from you telling your crush. Even if he or she is not interested, at least you can move on and stop wasting time on her or him.

context: To dream that your crush has died
meaning: suggests that your feelings for her or him is waning; the crush is no longer as strong. The dream may also be telling you to move on.

context: If you dream that somebody has a crush on you,
meaning: then it represents you own sense of worthiness and esteem.

context: To dream about a former crush
meaning: refers to a particular period in your life and what you were feeling then. Perhaps a waking relationship is repeating the same pattern.

context: To dream that your crush rejects you or stands you up
meaning: represents your feelings of insecurities and anxieties. The idea of not knowing how your crush feels about you is driving you nuts. Assuming that he or she rejects you, before you actually know how he or she feels, saves you from getting hurt. Because you are afraid to find out how he or she really feels about you, it may just be easier to move on if you think that they don't like you back.

context: To dream that you are on crutches
meaning: signify your need to lean on others for help. Perhaps you are acting helpless in order to get out of some situation or obligation.

context: To dream that you are crying
meaning: signifies a release of negative emotions that is more likely caused by some waking situation rather than the events of the dream itself. Your dream is a way to regain some emotional balance and to safely let out your fears and frustrations. In your daily lives, you tend to ignore, deny, or repress your feelings. But in your dream state, your defense mechanisms are no longer on guard and thus allow for the release of those feelings that you have repressed during the day.

context: To see someone else crying in your dream
meaning: may be a projection of your own feelings onto someone else. If you do not cry in your waking life, then seeing someone else cry may be a little easier to deal with then seeing yourself cry.

context: To wake up crying
meaning: represents some suppressed hurt or previous trauma that is coming up to the surface. You can no longer suppress these emotions. They need to be dealt with head on.

context: To dream that no one hears or responds to your cries
meaning: represents your helplessness, difficulties and frustrations in trying to communicate with others. You feel that your words are falling on deaf ears. Perhaps your dream is telling you to be more vocal and work harder to get your point across.

context: To dream that you are being cryopreserved
meaning: indicates that you may be stuck in the past. You are dwelling on how things used to be.

context: To see a crystal in your dream
meaning: signifies wholeness, purity, healing, development and unity. It represents your higher Self. The dream may be a metaphor for something in your life that is crystallizing or taking shape.

context: To dream that you are looking into a crystal
meaning: represents how you are looking within yourself to find your true destiny. Alternatively, it indicates your outlook of the future.

context: To see or look through a crystal ball in your dream
meaning: suggests that you are looking for guidance and direction in your life. It represents your outlook of the future.

context: To see or find a crystal skull in your dream
meaning: represents something you do not fully understand.

context: Dreaming that your own skull is turning into a crystal skull
meaning: suggests that you feel others can read your mind or see right through you. Perhaps you have something to hide. Alternatively, the dream symbolizes reflection, insight, intuition and mental powers. You need to look at a situation from the past, present and future.

context: To see a cub in your dream
meaning: represents innocence, playfulness and/or mischievousness. It is also symbolic of your children or siblings.

context: To see a cube in your dream
meaning: symbolizes material possessions and earthly things. It may also be a metaphor for "being square" or being too conservative.

context: To see a cuckoo in your dream
meaning: symbolizes unfaithfulness. Or there may be someone in your life whose presence is unwelcome. Perhaps you are the one who is intruding on other people's business. Alternatively, a cuckoo represents timing and fate. You need to change your direction or alter your approach in how your pursue some situation. The dream may also be a metaphor for someone who is behaving crazily.

context: To see or eat a cucumber in your dream
meaning: signifies recuperation and recovery. You need to regain your energy and health. Alternatively, it is symbolic of the phallus and have sexual connotations.

context: To dream that you are cuddling with someone
meaning: indicates your need for physical and/or emotional contact. Do not overlook the obvious meaning of this dream which suggests your heart's desire for that particular person. Also consider the symbolism of that person you are cuddling with and determine how you need to acknowledge, accept, and unify those qualities in yourself.

context: To dream that you are in a cult
meaning: suggests that you are in some destructive and/or manipulative relationship. You are being exploited. On a more positive note, you have the desire to strive for a better Self. It implies devotion and sense of community.

context: To see a cult in your dream
meaning: indicates that you are lacking any spiritual freedom.

context: To dream that you are a leader of a cult
meaning: signifies your authoritarian attitude. No one should question your motives or choices.

context: To dream that you are cultivating
meaning: indicates that you need to clear your mind of negative thoughts. Keeping an open mind will further allow you to grow as a person.

context: To see a cup in your dream
